<title>Marywood College</title>

</head>



<body background="/images/backgrnd.gif">

<img src="/images/mwlogos.jpg" align=left hspace=10>

<h1>Marywood College</h1>

<h2>Presuppositions, Goals and Objectives</h1>

<br clear=left><hr>


<h3>Presuppositions</h3><p>

The goals of education at Marywood are based on the following 
presuppositions:

<ul>

<li>that a personal, loving God exists.

<li>that each human person is sacred, called by God to become free, authentic 
and moral.

<li>that all human persons are entitled to respect, encouragement in the 
ongoing pursuit of learning and 

support in assessing their own potentialities and values in a free and 
responsible way.

<li>that a fully human development implies a response to God, love of 
oneself and action undertaken with 

others to help create conditions for human well-being throughout the global 
community.

<li>that unprecedented contemporary challenges exist in the evolving world 
of nature, technology, socio-economic and political system.

<li>that contemporary challenges must be addressed in both personal and 
professional contexts and that 

each individual is capable of responding constructively to these challenges.

</ul>



<h3>Goals</h3><p>

The Marywood College community aims to achieve the following goals:

<ul>

<li>to provide an education directed toward the self-development of a fully 
human person--one who 

responds not only to self, but also to others;  to the natural, the
technological, 
the political and the socio-

economic environment and to God.

<li>to pursue truth in the arts, sciences, humanities, philosophy and theology 
in a free and responsible 

manner.

<li>to pursue academic excellence through outstanding teaching and the 
promotion of research and 

community service on the national and international level.

<li>to integrate the tradition of liberal arts education with professional 
specialization.

<li>to provide an effective learning environment for all with particular 
awareness of the needs of women and first generation college students.

<li>to foster effective concern for environmental well-being, justice, peace, 
compassion and 

commitment to their promotion in the contemporary world.

<li>to develop competencies for responsible leadership, creativity and service 
in meeting human needs.

<li>to develop critical and creative thinking, aesthetic appreciation and 
independent learning skills.

</ul>



<h3>Objectives</h3><p>

In order to achieve these goals, Marywood pursues the following objectives:

<ul>

<li>to provide the context for the exploration and appreciation of the 
religious dimension of life through 

academic activities and a campus lifestyle that promotes the College's 
mission.

<li>to foster an awareness and appreciation of the pluralistic nature of 
contemporary societies through 

interdisciplinary studies and experiences that focus on international and 
multicultural diversity.

<li>to examine contemporary questions in the light of the wisdom of human 
tradition and to evaluate the 

relevancy and applicability of inherited insights through course work and 
other educational and research 

opportunities.

<li>to provide opportunities for aesthetic development and enjoyment for 
the College community and the 

surrounding region through academic offerings and the presentation of 
artistic, musical and theatrical 

programs.

<li>to provide means for the development of capacities for leadership and 
service through academic 

programs, campus activities and opportunities for community involvement.

<li>to foster critical and creative thinking in both the theoretical and
practical 
aspects of life by offering the appropriate liberal arts and professional 
programs.

<li>to provide opportunities for continuing professional and personal 
development through a range of 

educational experiences.

<li>to offer programs at off-campus as well as main campus locations.

</ul>

<hr>

