<!-- $MVD$:COLOR("16","7f7f7f","Dk Grey") -->
<!-- $MVD$:COLOR("17","c0c0c0","Lt Grey") --><BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF>

<P><IMG SRC="http://www.marywood.edu/images/mwlogos.jpg" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 VSPACE=0 HSPACE=10></P>
<H1>Marywood College</H1>
<H2><FONT SIZE=6>D</FONT><FONT SIZE=4>OCTORAL</FONT> <FONT SIZE=6>P</FONT><FONT SIZE=4>ROGRAM</FONT> <FONT
 SIZE=4>IN</FONT> <FONT SIZE=6>H</FONT><FONT SIZE=4>UMAN</FONT> <FONT SIZE=6>D</FONT><FONT SIZE=4>EVELOPMENT</FONT>
<BR></H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><HR ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100% SIZE=2></CENTER></P>
<P><B>The Counseling Psychology Specialization</B> is designed especially for the
 person who is currently licensed as a psychologist in the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania,
 as well as for those seeking an academic career in counseling psychology or for 
whom licensure is not an immediate goal. The Counseling Psychology faculty are exploring
 the future development of offerings which would be consistent with requirements 
for licensure.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>P</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2><B>ROGRAM</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=4><B> </B></FONT><FONT
 SIZE=5><B>D</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2><B>ESCRIPTION</B></FONT></CENTER></P>
<P>This sixty-credit program, leading to the degree of Doctor of Philosophy (Ph.D.),
 combines an interdisciplinary core, team-taught and common to all students, with
 discipline-based areas of concentrated specialization. Particular course titles 
are tentative and may change, but the components of the Doctoral Program in Human
 Development are:</P>
<P><B>I. The Interdisciplinary Core (15 credits)</B></P>
<P><UL>
<P><LI><A HREF="course.htm#hd1021">Human Development 1021 </A>-- Development and 
Change: Foundations for the Practitioner (4 credits)</LI>
<LI><A HREF="course.htm#hd1031">Human Development 1031</A> -- Social and Economic
 Dimensions of Human Development (4 credits)</LI>
<LI><A HREF="course.htm#hd1041">Human Development 1041</A> -- The Physiological and
 Psychological Basis of Human Development (4 credits)</LI>
<LI><A HREF="course.htm#hd1051">Human Development 1051</A> -- Selected Topics Seminar
 (3 credits)</LI>
</UL>
<P><B>II. The Research Core (9 credits)</B></P>
<P><UL>
<P><LI><A HREF="course.htm#hd1011">Advanced Statistical Analysis I 1011</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#hd1013">Advanced Statistical Analysis II 1013</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#hd1014">Qualitative Research 1014</A>
</LI></UL>
<P><B>III. The Specializations (27 credits)</B></P>
<P><UL>
<P><LI><I>The Counseling Psychology Specialization</I>
<BR><UL><LI>Advanced Clinical Courses (15 credits )<BR>
<UL><LI><A HREF="course.htm#asspsy">Assessment and Psychopathology Seminars</A> (6
 credits)</LI>
<LI><A HREF="course.htm#adjpsy">Seminar in Adjustment and Psychopathology</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#intass">Integrating Seminar on Assessment</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#adt">Assessment, Diagnosis and Treatment</A>
</LI></UL></LI>
<LI>Intervention Seminars (9 credits)<BR>
<UL><LI><A HREF="course.htm#profeth">Professional Ethics</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#ais">Advanced Intervention Strategies</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#brether">Brief Therapy</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#cogther">Cognitive Therapy</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#BMHP">Behavioral Medicine and Health Psychology</A>
</LI></UL></LI>
<LI><A HREF="course.htm#aps">Advanced Psychology Seminars (3 credits)</A>
</LI><LI>Practica (6 credits)<BR>
<UL><LI><A HREF="course.htm#psypract1">Practicum I &amp; II (Required)</A>
</LI><LI><A HREF="course.htm#psypract2">Practicum III &amp; IV (Elective)</A>
</LI></UL></LI>
<LI><A HREF="course.htm#psypredoc">Dissertation Research (9 credits) and Predoctoral
 Internship</A>
</LI></UL></LI>
</UL>
<P><B>IV. Comprehensive Examination</B></P>
<P>Upon completion of thirty credits (twelve interdisciplinary core credits, nine
 research credits and nine specialization credits) the student will take a qualifying
 exam. The exam may be in the form of an integrative paper written in response to
 a question or a series of questions provided by the faculty.</P>
<P><B>V. The Dissertation (9 credits)</B>
<BR><HR ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100% SIZE=2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>[<A HREF="/">Marywood's Home Page</A>] [<A HREF="/websites.htm">Other Places</A>]</CENTER></P>
