<H1>Marywood College</H1>
<H2>Marywood Today<BR></H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><HR ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=100% SIZE=2></CENTER></P>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>Thursday, November 7, 1996</CENTER></H1>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>MASSES</B></CENTER></P>
<PRE> <BR><B>Monday</B>                   <B>7:30 a.m.</B>      <B>Mary T. McNulty</B><BR><B>Rev. Duggan</B>                             <B>Sr. Martin de Porres McHale</B><BR><B>Rev. Wright</B>              <B>12:05 p.m.</B>     <B>Ross Scalese</B><BR><B>                                        Eleanor &amp; Children</B><BR>Tuesday                  7:30 a.m.      Patrick C. Hennigan<BR>Rev. Kang                               Shannon Keith<BR>Rev. Wright              12:05 p.m.     Frank Colandro<BR>                                        Irene Colandro<BR>Wednesday                7:30 a.m.      M/M Gordon Dion<BR>Rev. Kang                               Sr. Dolores M. Filicko, I.H.M.<BR>Rev. Wright              12:05 p.m.     Paul Surace<BR>                                        Andrew &amp; Mary Yaniga<BR>Thursday                 7:30 a.m.      Special Intentions of Agnes Azzarian<BR>                                        A Friend<BR>Rev. Everling            12:05 p.m.     Deceased Graduates &amp; Friends of Marywood<BR>                                        Marywood Development Office<BR>Friday                   7:30 a.m.      Helen Beckage<BR>Rev. Kang                               Sr. Martin de Porres McHale<BR>Rev. Duggan              12:05 p.m.     Louis Costanzo<BR>                                        Sr. Roberta Peters<BR><BR></PRE>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>MARYWOOD SNOWLINE</B></CENTER></P>
<P>Call the Marywood SNOWLINE, 961-4SNO, for updated closing, cancellation, &amp;
 delay announcements for Marywood College. Information will also be given to most
 local TV &amp; radio stations. Classes will be delayed or canceled if significant
 snow accumulations occur. Other weather problems will be dealt with as determined
 prudent. Students are advised to use their own discretion regarding travel to the
 campus.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>TODAY'S MEETINGS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Big Brothers/Big Sisters Informational meeting</B>, 9 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth
 Student Center. Agenda: Opportunities available with teenagers in Scranton area 
on &amp; off-campus.</P>
<P><B>Pink Bunnies Need Not Apply (The Marywood College Photography Club) meeting</B>,
 9 p.m., VAC 103. Agenda: Members are to bring photographs taken with disposable cameras.</P>
<P><B>Volunteers In Action meeting</B>, 9 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student Center.</P>
<P><B>Ski Club meeting</B>, 9 p.m., Pink Lounge, Nazareth Student Center.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>UPCOMING MEETINGS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Kappa Delta Pi,</B> 11/19, 9 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student Center.</P>
<P><B>Commuter Committee meeting</B>, 11/19, 8:45 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student
 Center. Everyone welcome. Agenda: Please bring food for the Thanksgiving Food Basket.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>DEPARTMENT NOTES</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Registration for the Spring, '97, semester</B> will continue today for the 
Class of 2000.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>CAMPUS/CLUB EVENTS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Candy bar sale</B>, $1 each, proceeds benefit the International Service Trip
 to Peru. Sponsored by the Collegiate Volunteers. Stop by their office in Regina 
Hall. Varieties include Krackle, Reese's Peanut Butter Cups, Kit Kat, Snickers, M&amp;M's.</P>
<P><B>Sign up for the Resident Christmas Dinner will take place</B> in the Pink Lounge
 during lunch, 11 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. &amp; dinner, 4:30 to 6 p.m., hours, as follows:
 <B>Today, commuters &amp; seniors</B>; 11/19, juniors; 11/20, sophomores; 11/21,
 freshmen; 11/22, all those who wish to go but missed their scheduled sign up date.</P>
<P><B>Starving Artists Sale</B>, 11/19, 11 a.m. to 7 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth 
Student Center. Prices range from $2 to $50. Wide variety of undergraduate &amp; 
graduate student artwork.</P>
<P><B>Faculty Preview Sessions for FULLTEXT Databases</B> sponsored by Marywood's
 Library Services are scheduled as follows: 11/19, 2 p.m.; 11/20, 9 a.m.; 11/21, 
Noon &amp; 4 p.m. Please R.S.V.P. to 348-6211, ext. 2546, or ext. 2365, 348-6264.</P>
<P><B>Grand Opening of FULLTEXT Databases</B>, 11/21, 11 a.m. to 3 p.m., Reference
 Area, main floor, LRC. Everyone is welcome to attend. Door prizes &amp; goodies!
 Sponsored by Marywood's Library Services.</P>
<P><B>Holiday Food Drive! </B>Monetary &amp; non-perishable donations now being accepted
 at the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall.</P>
<P><B>Big Brothers/Big Sisters representative will speak tonight</B> at 9 p.m. in
 the Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student Center. Topic will be on opportunities available
 for college students.</P>
<P><B>The Creativity Project, presented by Dave Binder</B>, 1/25, 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.,
 Crystal Room, Nazareth Student Center. Registration fee is $3 per person &amp; includes
 lunch. Limited space! Sign up by 12/9 in the Student Activities &amp; Leadership
 Office, Nazareth Student Center. This fun, inter-active leadership program is sponsored
 by Marywood College &amp; the University of Scranton.</P>
<P><B>Tri-Generation Christmas Social</B>, 12/6, 3 to 4:30 p.m., at the Marian Convent
 on campus. Join in arts &amp; crafts &amp; carols with senior citizens, college 
students &amp; elementary school children. Sign up outside of the Collegiate Volunteers
 Office, Regina Hall, or just meet in the Pink Lounge, Nazareth Student Center, on
 12/6 at 2:30 p.m.</P>
<P><B>Marywood's P.S.E.A. club will be selling long-sleeve t-shirts for $12 each</B> 
on 11/19, 20 &amp; 21, Noon to 4 p.m. in the HSC. If interested, but cannot make 
the sale, leave a message for Michelle in the P.S.E.A. mailbox in the Nazareth Student
 Center.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>CAREER INFORMATION</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>American Management Systems, Inc., Fairfax, VA, has current openings in their
 Computer Information Technology Department.</B> Graduating Computer Science majors
 or other graduating students with a strong background &amp; interest in computers
 who are interested in employment with A.M.S. are asked to submit their resume to
 the Career Services Office, Nazareth Student Center, no later than 11/20.</P>
<P><B>Students interested in employment with QVC, the world's leader in the electronic
 retail industry, are asked to</B> inquire at the Career Services Office, Nazareth
 Student Center, by 11/20. Marywood has been selected as a top choice institution
 for recruiting by this West Chester, PA, based organization.</P>
<P><B>A representative from the School District of Philadelphia will be on campus
 12/4</B> to recruit graduating Elementary Education &amp; Secondary Education majors.
 If interested, come to the Career Services Office, Nazareth Student Center, to sign
 up no later that 11/22. Credential files &amp; resume must also be completed by 
that date.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>SPORTS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Congratulations to Women's Volleyball player, Jill Sharer</B>, for being selected
 to the Pennsylvania Athletic Conference Women's Volleyball All-Conference Team.</P>
<P><B>Congratulations to Field Hockey players Jessie Fries &amp; Amy Tichy</B> for
 being named to the Pennsylvania Athletic Conference Field Hockey All-Conference 
First Team.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>FYI</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>The front entrance to the Regina Hall Chapel &amp; Campus Ministry Offices </B>is
 open Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Weekends upon request.</P>
<P><B>LRC Thanksgiving Break Schedule:</B> 11/26, 8 a.m. to 10 p.m. &amp; 11/27, 
8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.; 11/28, 29 &amp; 30, closed; 12/1, 1 to 10 p.m.</P>
<P><B>Honor Students are sent congratulations on</B> the over 100 surveys that have
 been returned to date. The information will be most helpful, however, Sr. Dorothy
 really needs to hear from everyone, especially those who took one or two courses
 in the past &amp; have not been active in the program lately. If you have not yet
 returned your survey, please take 10 or 15 minutes now to answer the questions &amp;
 return it to Sr. Dorothy Haney, LAC 120.</P>
<P><B>Tutors needed in all subjects for Spring, '97. </B>You must have received a
 B+ or an A average. Paid position. Tutor workshops will be held in January. Stop
 by the Academic Excellence Center, LRC 330, for an application.</P>
<P><B>Club officers planning an event or having a meeting in December who would like
 it published in the December Student Activities Calendar are asked to</B> send all
 information to Helen Rombalski in the Student Activities &amp; Leadership Development
 Office, Nazareth Student Center, by 11/21.</P>
<P><B>English majors needed to tutor at the Academic Excellence Center's Writing 
Center, LRC 330, for Spring, '97.</B> New hours are 1 to 3 p.m. &amp; 8 to 10 p.m.,
 Monday through Thursday, &amp; Sunday, 7 to 10 p.m. Paid position. Blocks of time
 can be shared. Stop by the Academic Excellence Center to inquire.</P>
<P><B>Current commuter students who would like to reside on campus for the Spring
 semester are asked to</B> stop by the Residence Life Office, Nazareth Student Center,
 before 12/13.</P>
<P><B>Volunteers In Action Fund-raiser forms &amp; money are now overdue! Please 
return them to the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall, A.S.A.P.! Forms &amp;
 money not returned today will NOT be ordered.</B></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>ENTERTAINMENT/CULTURAL EVENTS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>General Recital</B>, 11/20, 8:30 p.m., PAC 104. Free &amp; open to the public!
 The program is varied with both instrumentalists &amp; vocalists performing.</P>
<P><B>Symphony Ball</B>, 11/22, 9 p.m. to 1 a.m., Main Dining Room, Nazareth Student
 Center. Tickets are on sale now for $25 per couple or $13 per single in the Main
 Dining Room at meal time or from St. Cecelia members.</P>
<P><B>Quebec Ski Trip</B>, 1/5 through 10, $324 based on four per room, leave from
 Marywood on 1/5. If interested, leave a message for Amy Miller in the Ski Club mailbox
 in the Nazareth Student Center, or Amy's mailbox in Regina Hall.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>OTHER</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B><U>Collegiate Volunteers Opportunities:</U></B></P>
<P><UL>
<P><LI>High school student needs help in Calculus, has transportation to Marywood;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to help at the Thanksgiving Dinner for Scranton's elderly &amp;
 less fortunate on 11/26, opportunities available throughout the day;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed 11/27 to prepare/distribute food baskets in Scranton;</LI>
<LI>A representative from the Boys Hope/Girls Hope, a post-college service opportunity,
 will be in the area 12/5;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to help with various aspects of &quot;juice&quot; concert on
 11/23 from 8 p.m. to after Midnight;</LI>
<LI>Shop the Waverly Woman's Club Attic Shop for bargains, every Wednesday &amp; 
Friday, 10 a.m. to Noon until May, at the Waverly Community House, proceeds go to
 charity;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed for a Children's Hour with children from the Valley View Housing
 Development, 11/19, 3:30 to 4:30 p.m.;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to wrap Holiday gifts at The Mall at Steamtown, proceeds benefit
 the Neonatal Care Unit at the Community Medical Center, people needed in three hour
 shifts from 12/1 to 12/24, share your Holiday Spirit!</LI>
</UL>
<P>If interested in any of the above, call or stop by the Collegiate Volunteers Office,
 Regina Hall, 348-6211.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>SPECIALS</B></CENTER></P>
