<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>TODAY'S MEETINGS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Kappa Delta Pi,</B> 9 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student Center.</P>
<P><B>Commuter Committee meeting</B>, 11/19, 8:45 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student
 Center. Everyone welcome. Agenda: Please bring food for the Thanksgiving Food Basket.</P>
<P><B>P.H.E.A.A. Grants Informational meeting</B>, 8 p.m., Lynett Board Room, Nazareth
 Student Center. Agenda: Letter-writing campaign to Gov. Ridge &amp; the General 
Assembly in support of the P.H.E.A.A. program. If interested but unable to attend,
 please call Holly Alexander in the Residence Life Office, Nazareth Student Center,
 348-6246.</P>
<P><B>Women's Committee meeting</B>, Noon, Main Dining Room window side, Nazareth
 Student Center. Everyone welcome!</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>UPCOMING MEETINGS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>P.S.E.A. meeting</B>, 11/20, 2:30 p.m., HSC 104. Agenda: Those signed up for
 Holocaust trip are asked to please bring their money.</P>
<P><B>Science Department Student/Faculty meeting</B>, 11/20, 2 p.m., CNHS 203.</P>
<P><B>Student Dietetic Association meeting</B>, 11/20, 2 p.m., LAC 200.</P>
<P><B>Class of 2000 meeting</B>, 11/20, 8:30 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student 
Center. Agenda: Class Christmas tree ornament.</P>
<P><B>Math Club meeting</B>, 11/20, 2 p.m., CNHS 120.</P>
<P><B>Delta Epsilon Sigma dual-session meeting</B>, 11/21 at 2:30 p.m. or 11/22 at
 2 p.m., both in LAC 122. Agenda: Planning of activities.</P>
<P><B><I>Bayleaf</I></B><B> Staff meeting</B>, 11/20, 2 p.m., The Woods, Nazareth
 Student Center.</P>
<P><B>Undecided Majors Department meeting</B>, 11/20, 2 p.m., LAC 127. Agenda: Presentations
 will be offered from the Psychology, Nursing, Communication Arts, Nutrition &amp;
 Dietetics, Family &amp; Consumer Science Education Departments. Additional Department
 representatives will be invited to the 12/18 meeting.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>DEPARTMENT NOTES</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Registration for Spring, '97, semester</B> will be held today for the Class
 of 2001.</P>
<P><B>Transfers on probation &amp; all other unclassified students</B> in the Undergraduate
 School or the School of Continuing Education may register today for the Spring, 
'97, semester.</P>
<P><B>All sophomore, junior or graduate students interested in applying to the Coordinated
 Program in Nutrition &amp; Dietetics are asked to</B> report to LAC 227 on 11/25
 at Noon.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>CAMPUS/CLUB EVENTS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Sign up for the Resident Christmas Dinner will take place</B> in the Pink Lounge
 during lunch, 11 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. &amp; dinner, 4:30 to 6 p.m., hours, as follows:
 <B>Today, juniors</B>; 11/20, sophomores; 11/21, freshmen; 11/22, all those who 
wish to go but missed their scheduled sign up date.</P>
<P><B>Starving Artists Sale</B>, today, 11 a.m. to 7 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth 
Student Center. Prices range from $2 to $50. Wide variety of undergraduate &amp; 
graduate student artwork.</P>
<P><B>Faculty Preview Sessions for FULLTEXT Databases</B> sponsored by Marywood's
 Library Services are scheduled as follows: Today, 2 p.m.; 11/20, 9 a.m.; 11/21, 
Noon &amp; 4 p.m. Please R.S.V.P. to 348-6211, ext. 2546, or ext. 2365, 348-6264.</P>
<P><B>Grand Opening of FULLTEXT Databases</B>, 11/21, 11 a.m. to 3 p.m., Reference
 Area, main floor, LRC. Everyone is welcome to attend. Door prizes &amp; goodies!
 Sponsored by Marywood's Library Services.</P>
<P><B>Holiday Food Drive! </B>Monetary &amp; non-perishable donations now being accepted
 at the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall.</P>
<P><B>50/50 raffle tickets on sale now</B>, $1 each, drawing is 12/4 (just in time
 for the Holidays!). Stop by the Collegiate Volunteers or Campus Ministry Offices,
 Regina Hall, or call 348-6211, ext. 2419 or ext. 4723.</P>
<P><B>Santa's Workshop</B>, 12/5, 6, 9 &amp; 10, 9 a.m. to 6 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth
 Student Center. Do your Christmas shopping on campus! Toys, household items, knick-knacks
 available.</P>
<P><B>Consult about writing assignments at</B> the Academic Excellence Center, LRC
 330, as follows: Tuesday through Thursday, 10 to 11:30 a.m. &amp; 1 to 8 p.m. &amp;
 Monday, 10 to 11:30 a.m. &amp; 1 to 4 p.m.</P>
<P><B>The Miller Analogy Exam</B> has been scheduled for 11/20 &amp; 12/10 at 4 p.m.
 in the HSC. Reservations can be made by calling Mrs. Flaherty at 348-6269.</P>
<P><B>Chi Alpha Epsilon Craft Show</B>, today &amp; 11/20, 8 a.m. to 9 p.m., Crystal
 Room, Nazareth Student Center. Talented area crafters with beautiful gift ideas 
for the whole family will be featured.</P>
<P><B>Comprehensive Social Sciences Study Group</B>, Tuesdays at 6 p.m. &amp; Thursdays
 at 7 p.m., Academic Excellence Center, LRC 330.</P>
<P><B>Raffle tickets on sale now from the M.S.W. Student Association members or LAC
 81. </B>All proceeds to benefit Job Link. Drawing to be held 12/5. Prizes are: 1st
 prize, Hand-made Afghan; 2nd prize, $25 cash; 3rd prize, Hand-decorated Hat Boxes;
 4th prize, $10 Price Chopper Gift Certificate.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>CAREER INFORMATION</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>American Management Systems, Inc., Fairfax, VA, has current openings in their
 Computer Information Technology Department.</B> Graduating Computer Science majors
 or other graduating students with a strong background &amp; interest in computers
 who are interested in employment with A.M.S. are asked to submit their resume to
 the Career Services Office, Nazareth Student Center, no later than 11/20.</P>
<P><B>Students interested in employment with QVC, the world's leader in the electronic
 retail industry, are asked to</B> inquire at the Career Services Office, Nazareth
 Student Center, by 11/20. Marywood has been selected as a top choice institution
 for recruiting by this West Chester, PA, based organization.</P>
<P><B>Career Research Intern position available in the Career Services Office, Nazareth
 Student Center, for the Spring semester only.</B> Six credits of graduate tuition
 may be obtained for 12 hours of work per week. No stipend. Duties will involve research,
 input &amp; analysis of statistical data. Skills should include computer experience
 with Windows &amp; Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Access &amp; Powerpoint). Please
 inquire in the Career Services Office, Nazareth Student Center.</P>
<P><B>E.D.S. (Electronic Data Systems), Herndon, VA, is hiring computer personnel</B> 
&amp; will review resumes referred by Marywood. Graduating Computer Science majors
 interested in employment with E.D.S. are asked to submit their resume to the Career
 Services Office, Nazareth Student Center, no later than 12/15.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>STUDENT GOVERNMENT</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Thanksgiving Food Drive! </B>Please bring non-perishable food items &amp; place
 them in the Commuter Boxes located as follows: Outside of the First Stop in the 
LAC; outside of The Woods in the Nazareth Student Center; by the soda machines in
 the HSC &amp; at the entrance of the CNHS. Sponsored by the Commuter Committee.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>SPORTS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Marywood College's Business Club (The 1040's) vs. The Lackawanna County Bar
 Association's Young Lawyers Division Charity Basketball Game</B>, 11/24, 2 to 5 
p.m., Gym, H&amp;PE Center. Admission is $2 for adults or $1 with valid Marywood 
I.D. or for children under the age of 12. Proceeds to benefit The Scranton Counseling
 Center's Autism Project. Half-time activities include face-painting &amp; sand art
 for children &amp; a 50/50 raffle for adults.</P>
<P><B>Upcoming Intramural Deadlines: </B>12/11, 3 v. 3 Basketball Tournament; 12/12,
 4 v. 4 Indoor Wiffleball Tournament &amp; 4 v. 4 Volleyball Tournament. Sign up 
in the H&amp;PE Center.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>FYI</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>The front entrance to the Regina Hall Chapel &amp; Campus Ministry Offices </B>is
 open Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Weekends upon request.</P>
<P><B>Honor Students are sent congratulations on</B> the over 100 surveys that have
 been returned to date. The information will be most helpful, however, Sr. Dorothy
 really needs to hear from everyone, especially those who took one or two courses
 in the past &amp; have not been active in the program lately. If you have not yet
 returned your survey, please take 10 or 15 minutes now to answer the questions &amp;
 return it to Sr. Dorothy Haney, LAC 120.</P>
<P><B>Recreation Center Thanksgiving Holiday Hours: </B>11/27, open till 8 p.m.; 
11/28, 29, 30 &amp; 12/1, closed; 12/2, will re-open with regular hours.</P>
<P><B>The Campus Ministry Office is looking for 50 employee volunteers interested
 in </B>taking speaking parts or performing an action at the Thanksgiving Prayer 
Breakfast on 11/26 at 7:30 a.m. If interested, please call Sr. Maureen at ext. 4703.</P>
<P><B>Tutors are asked to s</B>top in at the Academic Excellence Center, LRC 330,
 to sign payroll before the Thanksgiving Recess. New candy supply.</P>
<P><B>Seniors are advised that</B> there is a <U>tentative</U> graduation list for
 <U>JANUARY, '97</U>, posted on the Undergraduate Dean's enclosed bulletin board 
in the LAC on the first floor stairwell between the LAC &amp; Regina Hall. Check 
for appropriate degree, correct name spelling &amp; designated hometown. Any questions
 or concerns are to be reported to the Dean's office, LAC 101, by 4:30 p.m. on 12/6.</P>
<P><B>The Academic Excellence Center's Writing Center's new hours for Spring, '97,
 are: </B>Monday through Thursday, 1 to 3 p.m. &amp; 8 to 10 p.m. &amp; Sunday, 7
 to 10 p.m.</P>
<P><B>All club advisors </B>whose group is planning a meeting &amp;/or special event
 for the month of December &amp; who would like it published in the December Student
 Activities Calendar, are asked to please send all information to Helen Rombalski
 in the Student Activities &amp; Leadership Development Office, Nazareth Student 
Center, by 11/21.</P>
<P><B>Anyone interested in joining or learning more about the Campus Ministry Social
 Justice Committee is asked to</B> leave a message for Mary Ann Lett in her mailbox
 located in the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall. This club's interests 
cover various social &amp; political aspects that may be of interest to many.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>ENTERTAINMENT/CULTURAL EVENTS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>&quot;WOMEN'S WORK: the art of contemporary female photographers&quot;</B>,
 on display now through 11/24 in the Contemporary Gallery, VAC. Free &amp; open to
 the public! This is a powerful exhibition of photographs by major artists &amp; 
it's also Marywood's first all-photography exhibit. Gallery hours are: Monday through
 Wednesday, 9 a.m. to 8 p.m.; Thursday &amp; Friday, 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.; Saturday &amp;
 Sunday, 1 to 4 p.m.</P>
<P><B>&quot;Romantic Old Vienna&quot;, concert featuring Marywood's Orchestra conducted
 by Mr. Robert Herrema</B>, 11/24, 7:30 p.m., PAC Auditorium. Free &amp; open to 
the public! Selections include: Brahms', Hungarian Dance no. 5; Mozart's, Violin 
Concerto no. 5 featuring soloist Amy Christian; J. Strauss, Sr.'s, Radetzky March;
 J. Strauss, Jr.'s, Blue Danube Waltz; &amp; Von Suppe's, Light Calvary Overture.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>OTHER</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B><U>Collegiate Volunteers Opportunities:</U></B>
<BR><UL><LI>High school student needs help in Calculus, has transportation to Marywood;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to help at the Thanksgiving Dinner for Scranton's elderly &amp;
 less fortunate on 11/26, opportunities available throughout the day;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed 11/27 to prepare/distribute food baskets in Scranton;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to wrap Holiday gifts at The Mall at Steamtown, proceeds benefit
 the Neonatal Care Unit at the Community Medical Center, people needed in three hour
 shifts from 12/1 to 12/24, share your Holiday Spirit!;</LI>
<LI>Elves needed to help with a Christmas Program &amp; Parade on 12/8 from 11:30
 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.;</LI>
<LI>Volunteer tutors needed for 4th grade general homework &amp; 6th grade Math;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to assist the Steamtown Volunteer Association with daily operation
 of its book store &amp; association at the Steamtown National Historic Site, days
 &amp; hours flexible;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed for survey distribution of residents in the Mulberry High-Rise,
 days &amp; hours flexible;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to help implement an HIV/AIDS youth group with the Lackawanna
 County AIDS Council, days &amp; hours vary;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed for various duties at the Green Ridge Nursing Home, Scranton,
 including visiting &amp; transporting residents, decorating &amp; activities, days
 &amp; hours flexible;</LI>
<LI>Allied Services in Clarks Summit, needs volunteers to help elderly with cleaning,
 cooking &amp; reading.</LI>
</UL>
<P>If interested in any of the above, call or stop by the Collegiate Volunteers Office,
 Regina Hall, 348-6211.</P>
<P><B>Phi Sigma Iota's informal group of Spanish-speakers, called Tertulia, will 
be gathering to practice their language skills through friendly conversation.</B> 
Any intermediate or advanced Spanish-speakers welcome. Anyone interested may gather
 at the Cafe del Sol, which is located on Mulberry Street in Scranton, on 11/22 at
 3 p.m. For more information, contact Dr. Victoria Jaen, LAC 120, 348-6211, ext. 2309.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>SPECIALS</B></CENTER></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>Tuesday</B>
<BR><B>Sausage &amp; Pepper On Hard Roll, Plum Tomato Salad</B></CENTER>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>Wednesday<BR>Grilled Cheese &amp; Bacon, Potato Salad</CENTER>
