<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>Wednesday, November 20, 1996</CENTER></H1>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>MASSES</B></CENTER></P>
<PRE> <BR><B>Wednesday</B>          <B>7:30 a.m.</B>          <B>M/M Gordon Dion</B><BR><B>Rev. Kang</B>                             <B>Sr. Dolores M. Filicko, I.H.M.</B><BR><B>Rev. Wright</B>        <B>12:05 p.m.</B>         <B>Paul Surace</B><BR>                                      <B>Andrew &amp; Mary Yaniga</B><BR>Thursday           7:30 a.m.          Special Intentions of Agnes Azzarian<BR>                                      A Friend<BR>Rev. Everling      12:05 p.m.         Deceased Graduates &amp; Friends of Marywood<BR>                                      Marywood Development Office<BR>Friday             7:30 a.m.          Helen Beckage<BR>Rev. Kang                             Sr. Martin de Porres McHale<BR>Rev. Duggan        12:05 p.m.         Louis Costanzo<BR>                                      Sr. Roberta Peters<BR>Sunday             3:30 p.m.          Barnard Cannon<BR>Rev. Bryan                            Sr. Maureen Cannon<BR>Monday             7:30 a.m.          In Thanksgiving<BR>                                      D. Yetkowskos<BR>Msgr. Essef        12:05 p.m.         Eileen &amp; Billy Walsh<BR>                                      Children<BR>Tuesday            7:30 a.m.          Thanksgiving Prayer Breakfast<BR>                                      (No Liturgy)<BR>Rev. Duggan        12:05 p.m.         Louis Costanzo<BR>                                      Mark &amp; Wendy Brenzel<BR><BR><BR></PRE>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>TODAY'S MEETINGS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>P.S.E.A. meeting</B>, 2:30 p.m., HSC 104. Agenda: Those signed up for Holocaust
 trip are asked to please bring their money; come see the new t-shirts.</P>
<P><B>Science Department Student/Faculty meeting</B>, 2 p.m., CNHS 203.</P>
<P><B>Student Dietetic Association meeting</B>, 2 p.m., LAC 200.</P>
<P><B>Class of 2000 meeting</B>, 8:30 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student Center.
 Agenda: Class Christmas tree ornament.</P>
<P><B>Math Club meeting</B>, 2 p.m., CNHS 120.</P>
<P><B><I>Bayleaf</I></B><B> Staff meeting</B>, 2 p.m., The Woods, Nazareth Student
 Center.</P>
<P><B>Undecided Majors Department meeting</B>, 2 p.m., LAC 127. Agenda: Presentations
 will be offered from the Psychology, Nursing, Communication Arts, Nutrition &amp;
 Dietetics, Family &amp; Consumer Science Education Departments. Additional Department
 representatives will be invited to the 12/18 meeting.</P>
<P><B>Cultural Diversity Committee meeting</B>, 3:45 p.m., LAC 120. Everyone invited.</P>
<P><B>C.E.C. meeting</B>, 2 p.m., HSC 102. Agenda: Speaker on job opportunities.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>UPCOMING MEETINGS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Delta Epsilon Sigma dual-session meeting</B>, 11/21 at 2:30 p.m. or 11/22 at
 2 p.m., both in LAC 122. Agenda: Planning of activities.</P>
<P><B>Volunteers In Action meeting</B>, 12/2, 9 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student
 Center. Agenda: End of the year Christmas Party.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>DEPARTMENT NOTES</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>All sophomore, junior or graduate students interested in applying to the Coordinated
 Program in Nutrition &amp; Dietetics are asked to</B> report to LAC 227 on 11/25
 at Noon.</P>
<P><B>Any Education majors needing experience in their field for for sophomore screening
 are asked to</B> stop by or call the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall, 
348-6211, ext. 2419. Opportunities are available with children, daycares, tutoring
 &amp; much more.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>CAMPUS/CLUB EVENTS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Sign up for the Resident Christmas Dinner will take place</B> in the Pink Lounge
 during lunch, 11 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. &amp; dinner, 4:30 to 6 p.m., hours, as follows:
 <B>Today, sophomores</B>; 11/21, freshmen; 11/22, all those who wish to go but missed
 their scheduled sign up date.</P>
<P><B>Faculty Preview Sessions for FULLTEXT Databases</B> sponsored by Marywood's
 Library Services are scheduled as follows: Today, 9 a.m.; 11/21, Noon &amp; 4 p.m.
 Please R.S.V.P. to 348-6211, ext. 2546, or ext. 2365, 348-6264.</P>
<P><B>Grand Opening of FULLTEXT Databases</B>, 11/21, 11 a.m. to 3 p.m., Reference
 Area, main floor, LRC. Everyone is welcome to attend. Door prizes &amp; goodies!
 Sponsored by Marywood's Library Services.</P>
<P><B>50/50 raffle tickets on sale now</B>, $1 each, drawing is 12/4 (just in time
 for the Holidays!). Stop by the Collegiate Volunteers or Campus Ministry Offices,
 Regina Hall, or call 348-6211, ext. 2419 or ext. 4723.</P>
<P><B>Santa's Workshop</B>, 12/5, 6, 9 &amp; 10, 9 a.m. to 6 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth
 Student Center. Do your Christmas shopping on campus! Toys, household items, knick-knacks
 available.</P>
<P><B>Chi Alpha Epsilon Craft Show</B>, today, 8 a.m. to 9 p.m., Crystal Room, Nazareth
 Student Center. Talented area crafters with beautiful gift ideas for the whole family
 will be featured.</P>
<P><B>Raffle tickets on sale now from the M.S.W. Student Association members or LAC
 81. </B>All proceeds to benefit Job Link. Drawing to be held 12/5. Prizes are: 1st
 prize, Hand-made Afghan; 2nd prize, $25 cash; 3rd prize, Hand-decorated Hat Boxes;
 4th prize, $10 Price Chopper Gift Certificate.</P>
<P><B>P.S.E.A. is selling long-sleeve t-shirts</B> for $12 each today &amp; 11/21
 from Noon to 4 p.m. in the HSC.</P>
<P><B>Candy Bar Sale</B>, $1 each, proceeds benefit the International Service Trip
 to Peru. Stop by the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall. Varieties include
 Krackle, Reese's Peanut Butter Cups, Kit Kat, Snickers, M&amp;M's.</P>
<P><B>Holiday Sale</B>, 11/22, 10 a.m. to 6 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student Center.
 Bath &amp; body products, fragrance, hair care, nail care, men's products, color
 cosmetics available. Get a jump on your Christmas shopping. (Men, shop for that 
special someone!).</P>
<P><B>Social hosted by &amp; in McCarty Hall to thank all those who participated 
in this year's annual Haunted House</B>, 11/21, 9:30 p.m. All those who helped by
 decorating, dressing up in costume &amp;/or cleaning up are invited to attend. Refreshments
 will be served.</P>
<P><B>Christmas Giving Trees</B>, located in the Foyer of Regina Hall &amp; the Blue
 Lounge in Nazareth Student Center. Take an ornament off of a tree, buy a $2 to $10
 gift for the person from a low-income family, bring wrapped gift to the Collegiate
 Volunteers Office, Regina Hall, or the Security Desk, Nazareth Student Center, by
 12/19. For more information, call 348-6211, ext. 2419.</P>
<P><B>Search Renewal,</B> 12/7, 6 p.m., Foyer, Regina Hall. For those who have already
 attended Search.</P>
<P><B>Bake Sale</B>, today &amp; 11/21, 11:30 a.m. to 1 p.m. in the Commons &amp;
 5:30 to 7:30 p.m. in the HSC; 11/22, 11:30 a.m. to 1 p.m. in the Commons. Sponsored
 by Marywood's Cheerleaders.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>CAREER INFORMATION</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>A representative from the School District of Philadelphia is coming to recruit
 graduating Elementary Education &amp; Secondary Education students on 12/4.</B> 
If interested, come to the Career Services Office, Nazareth Student Center, to sign
 up no later than 11/22. Credential files &amp; resumes must also be completed by
 that date.</P>
<P><B>Eastman Kodak Health Group will accept resumes from M.B.A. graduates with two
 to three years experience.</B> Positions include marketing, finance &amp; sales.
 Resumes should be scannable (on white paper in bold print) &amp; submitted to the
 Career Services Ofice, Nazareth Student Center, no later than 12/13.</P>
<P><B>Bell Atlantic has part-time openings available doing Directory Assistance Calling.</B> 
Interested students may inquire by calling 1-800-370-2626 or 215-466-3248. There 
is a possibility that is students are interested &amp; inquire, a Bell Atlantic representative
 may interview on campus. Further information is available in the Career Services
 Office.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>FYI</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>The front entrance to the Regina Hall Chapel &amp; Campus Ministry Offices </B>is
 open Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Weekends upon request.</P>
<P><B>Tutors are asked to </B>stop in at the Academic Excellence Center, LRC 330,
 to sign payroll before the Thanksgiving Recess. New candy supply.</P>
<P><B>Seniors are advised that</B> there is a <U>tentative</U> graduation list for
 <U>JANUARY, '97</U>, posted on the Undergraduate Dean's enclosed bulletin board 
in the LAC on the first floor stairwell between the LAC &amp; Regina Hall. Check 
for appropriate degree, correct name spelling &amp; designated hometown. Any questions
 or concerns are to be reported to the Dean's office, LAC 101, by 4:30 p.m. on 12/6.</P>
<P><B>Anyone interested in joining or learning more about the Campus Ministry Social
 Justice Committee is asked to</B> leave a message for Mary Ann Lett in her mailbox
 located in the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall. This club's interests 
cover various social &amp; political aspects that may be of interest to many.</P>
<P><B>English majors needed to tutor at the Academic Excellence Center's Writing 
Center for Spring, '97.</B> New hours are Monday through Thursday, 1 to 3 p.m. &amp;
 8 to 10 p.m.; Sunday, 7 to 10 p.m. Paid position. Blocks of time can be shared. 
Stop by the Academic Excellence Center, LRC 330, to inquire.</P>
<P><B>Club officers planning an event or having a meeting in December who would like
 it published in the December Student Activities Calendar are asked to</B> please
 send all information to Helen Rombalski, Student Activities &amp; Leadership Development
 Office, by 11/21.</P>
<P><B>Commuters are asked for their suggestions, comments &amp; concerns that are
 of interest to commuters.</B> Suggestion Boxes can be found on campus as follows:
 In the vending area in the HSC; the Student Lounge in the CNHS; outside of the entrance
 to The Woods &amp; in the Pink Lounge, both in the Nazareth Student Center; &amp;,
 outisde of the First Stop in the LAC. Sponsored by the Student Activities &amp; 
Leadership Development Office.</P>
<P><B>Tutors will be needed in all subjects for Spring, '97.</B> Must have received
 a B+ or an A average. Paid position. Tutor workshops will be held in January. Stop
 by the Academic Excellence Center, LRC 330, for an application.</P>
<P><B>There will not be a 10:30 a.m. Mass on Sundays until further notice. However</B>,
 there is once exception. On 12/8, there will be a 9 a.m. Mass.</P>
<P><B>LRC Thanksgiving Break Schedule:</B> 11/26, 8 a.m. to 10 p.m.; 11/27, 8 a.m.
 to 4:30 p.m.; 11/28, 29 &amp; 30, closed; 12/1, 1 to 10 p.m.</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>ENTERTAINMENT/CULTURAL EVENTS</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B>Quebec Ski Trip</B>, 1/5 throu 10/97, cost is $324 based on four per room, 
leave from Marywood on 1/5/97. If interested, leave a message for Amy Miller in the
 Ski Club mailbox located in the Nazareth Student Center, or in Amy's mailbox in 
Regina Hall.</P>
<P><B>General Recital</B>, tonight, 8:30 p.m., PAC 104. Free &amp; open to the public!
 The program is varied with instrumentalists &amp; vocalists performing.</P>
<P>&quot;<B>Dead Poets Society&quot;, movie</B>, tonight, 9 p.m., The Woods. FREE!</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>OTHER</B></CENTER></P>
<P><B><U>Collegiate Volunteers Opportunities:</U></B>
<BR><UL><LI>Elves needed to help with a Christmas Program &amp; Parade on 12/8 from
 11:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.;</LI>
<LI>Volunteer tutors needed for 4th grade general homework &amp; 6th grade Math;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed for survey distribution of residents in the Mulberry High-Rise,
 days &amp; hours flexible;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to help implement an HIV/AIDS youth group with the Lackawanna
 County AIDS Council, days &amp; hours vary;</LI>
<LI>Volunteers needed to join teens from the Scranton area for afternoons of fun,
 food &amp; games on 11/23 at 12:30 p.m. to 2:30 p.m.</LI>
</UL>
<P>If interested in any of the above, call or stop by the Collegiate Volunteers Office,
 Regina Hall, 348-6211.</P>
<P><B>Hiking Trip with Rev. Michael Hughes at Rickets Glen</B>, 11/23, 10 a.m. to
 3 p.m. Sign up outside of the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall. On 11/23,
 meet outside the front of Regina Hall at 10 a.m.</P>
