src="Graphics/calendar.gif" alt=""></h1></CENTER><br>
<h1>IHM Congregation Calendar of Events</h1>
1997<br>
| <a href="#january">January</a> | <a href="#february">February</a> | <a href="#march">March</a> | <a href="#april">April</a> | <a href="#may97">May</a> | <a href="#june">June</a> | <a href="#july">July</a> | <a href="#august">August</a> |
<P>
| <a href="Calendar/special.html">Special 
Events</a> | <a href="Calendar/cresco.html">IHM Spiritual Renewal 
Center</a> |</h2> 
<img src="Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
____________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<h2><a name="january">January</a></h2>
<img src="Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<dl>
<DT><H3>4 / Saturday</H3>

<DD><B>Membership and Governance Videoconference</B><BR>
Sponsored by the IHM Standing Committee on Governance<BR>
Baltimore, New York, Pittsburgh, Scranton<BR>
<img src="Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>10 - 12 / Friday - Sunday</H3>
<DD><b>DeMello Weekend Retreat</b><BR>
Anthony DeMello, SJ was an expert in teaching us how to be aware of God in the ordinary events of our life.  This weekend will focus on the prayer experience that DeMello left to us to help enrich our lives by being cognizant of how God is found in everyday happenings.<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Arrive:  Friday -- 7:00 p.m.
<LI>Depart:  Sunday -- 10:30 a.m.
</UL>
<BLOCKQUOTE>IHM Spiritual Renewal Center<BR>
Box 568, RR 1<BR>
Cresco, PA<BR>
717-595-7548</BLOCKQUOTE>
<img src="Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>

<DT><H3>12 / Sunday</H3>
<DD><b>New York Area IHM Social Justice Group Meeting</b><BR>
2:00 - 4:00 p.m.<BR>
St. Mary Convent<BR>
Manhasset, NY<BR>
For further information, contact Sr. Chris Koelhoffer at 212-475-6677<BR>

<P>
<DD><B>Women's Reflection on the Scriptures:  Art Exhibit and Opening Reception</B><BR>
<B>(Exhibit through March 18)</B><BR>
By WTU Theology and Arts Coordinator Celester Lauritsen, and artists Valerie Margolis, Ellouise Schoettler, Deborah Sokolove, Dorothy Masom, Sheila Pritchard, Sr. Mary Grace Thul, OP, Mary Trent Scott and Katherine Kenny Bayly.<BR>
2:00 - 4:00 p.m.<BR>
Washington Theological Union<BR>
For more information call 202-726-8800 or 800-334-9922<BR>

<img src="Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
