<title>Marywood College Business and Managerial Sciences</title>
</head>

<body background="/images/backgrnd.gif">
<img src="/images/mwlogos.jpg" align=left hspace=10>
<h1>Marywood College</h1>
<h2>Business and Managerial Sciences</h2>
<br clear=left><hr>

<ul>
<li><a href="#state">Statement of Philosophy</a>
<li><a href="#general">General Information</a>
<li><a href="#faculty">Faculty Qualifications</a>
<li><a href="/www2/busweb/programs.htm">Business Programs</a>
<li><a href="#intern">Internships</a>
<li><a href="#transfer">Transfer of Credits</a>
<li><a href="#planning">Program Planning</a>
<li><a href="#grad">Graduate Business Programs</a>
</ul>
<hr>

<img src="/www2/busweb/buslect2.jpg" align=left hspace=10>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<p>
If you're serious about a career in business, then you should seriously consider Marywood.
<br clear=left><hr>

<h3><a name="state">Statement of Philosophy<p></h3>
The undergraduate business program enables students to acquire competencies necessary for a career
 in a variety of organizations, such as financial services, marketing, manufacturing, information systems, 
human resources and governmental enterprises. <p>

<h3><a name="general">General Information<p></h3>
Do you imagine yourself succeeding as a business analyst, bank officer, stockbroker, accountant, administrator, insurance underwriter -- or anywhere in the exciting world of business?  
Then, you want a challenging career -- a career path that takes you beyond the year 2000 through Marywood's Business Programs.<p>

<h3><a name="faculty">Faculty Qualifications<p></h3>
Marywood's business faculty have the practical business experience to add credence to the academic 
knowledge they impart.  Possessing graduate degrees from a wide range of geographical areas, they 
present the various business philosophies both in the United States and in the international sector as 
applied to multi-national corporations.  These skilled professionals can help you invest your energy 
and abilities in an education that can pay dividends in a rewarding future.  The congenial atmosphere 
on campus is felt not only among the students but also by the faculty whose dedication is immediately 
apparent.<p>

<h3><a name="intern">Internships<p></h3>
All business students are strongly urged to take advantage of the excellent opportunities in work 
experience provided by the corporations who have agreed to participate in the internship program.  The 
unique on-the-job training gives students a chance to try out skills developed in the formal classroom.  
Students can sigh for the internship during their Junior or Senior year, however, their GPA in their 
major must be at least 3.0.<p>

Accounting students will have to do their internship during the Spring semester of their Senior year.<p>

<h3><a name="transfer">Transfer of Credits<p></h3>
Students transferring from other colleges/universities, upon acceptance, will be required to complete a 
minimum of 30 credit hours of their business courses at the Marywood College campus.<p>

<h3><a name="planning">Program Planning<p></h3>
All business majors must see their advisors and plan their program accordingly.  Since economics in a 
requirement of all business majors, the liberal arts courses in social sciences must be carefully selected 
by students and approved by their advisors.<p>

<h3><a name="grad">Graduate Business Programs<p></h3>
In a world of rapid change and advancing technologies, many undergraduate students may wish to 
continue their education through the master's degree programs.  The Marywood Graduate School of 
Arts and Sciences can help you continue your professional development and earn the Master of Business 
Administration (M.B.A.) degree, with areas of concentration in Finance and Investment, Management 
Information Systems, Industrial Management, International Business or Health Services Administration.
<p>
The Master of Science option is available for those students concentrating in the computer aspects of 
information systems.  For more information on Marywood master's degree programs, contact the 
<i>Executive Director of the Graduate Business and Managerial Science Program</i> at 717-348-6274 
or write to:<br>
<tt>Graduate Admissions<br>
Marywood College<br>
Scranton, PA 18509</tt>.<p>


