<title>Marywood College</title>
</head>

<body background="/images/backgrnd.gif">
<img src="/images/mwlogos.jpg" align=left hspace=10>
<h1>Marywood College</h1>
<h2>Department of Foreign Languages</h2>
<br clear=left><hr>

<h2><i>Foreign Languages...your passport to success.</i></h2>
<hr>
<b>STATEMENT OF PHILOSOPHY</b><br>
In order to leave responsibly in an interdependent world where scientific and
technological
advances are breaking down national boundaries, students must learn to
understand, appreciate and
respect other languages and cultures. The student who is able to communicate in
other language
develops a world consciousness, an increased cultural awareness that enables
the student to pursue
truth with more understanding of social concern for others. Improved
communication skills
provide better understanding of our partners in interdependence.<p>

<b>PROGRAMS</b><br>
The Department of Foreign Languages offers a major program in French and
Spanish. The
department also offers a major in International Business in cooperation with
the Department of
Business and Managerial Science.
A minor in TESOL (Teaching of English to Speakers of Other Languages) is
designed to prrovide
students with the professional training necessary to work effectively with
students whose language
is not English.<p>

<b>FACULTY QUALIFICATIONS</b>  <br>
Marywood's foreign language faculty is made up of highly qualified professors,
able to provide an
in-depth understanding of the culture and people of the country whose language
they teach. All
have studied, traveled or lived in those countries.<p>

<b>STUDIES ABROAD</b> <br>
The Department of Foreign Languages has a study abroad advisor who gives
students individual
assistance in selecting a study abroad program which matches their particular
needs. All students
are strongly encouraged to spend either a semester, a summer, or a year abroad
to deepen their
understanding of the culture as well as the language. <p>

<hr>
