<h3>IV. PROFESSIONAL CONTRIBUTION (NO CREDIT) </h3>
<b>ART 555, ART 555E or ART 555W:</b> Students are required to select one of the 
culminating experiences at a designated time prior to graduation. It may be a 
research paper, creative project or an exhibit.<p>

<hr>
<H2>Master of Arts in Art Therapy</H2>
48 semester hours<BR>

The Marywood Art Therapy program follows the guidelines of the American Art 
Therapy Association.<p>

The core of the curriculum consists of courses in both art therapy and 
psychology. Thirty-three credits in Art Therapy and fifteen credits in 
Psychology are required.<p>

<h3>I. REQUIRED COURSES: (33 credits in Art Therapy, 15 credits in Psychology)</h3>
*A T 520 Introduction to Art Therapy 	 3<BR>
*A T 528 Pyschology of Art 	 3<BR>
*A T 532 Studio in Art Therapy 	 3<BR>
*A T 523 Child Case Studies in Art Therapy 	 3<BR>
*A T 522 Art Therapy Skills 	 3<BR>
*A T 538 Group Supervision in Art Therapy 	 0<BR>
*A T 540ABCD Practicum in Art Therapy 	 1.5, 1.5, 1.5, 1.5<BR>
*A T 539 Group Process in Art Therapy 	 0<BR>
*A T 526 Adult Case Studies in Art Therapy 	 3<BR>
*A T 527 Art Therapy Literature 	 3<BR>
*A T 531 Introduction to Family Art Therapy 	 3<BR>
*A T 530 Art in Special Education 	 3<BR>
*PSY 517 Personality Theories 	 3<BR>
*PSY 531 Psychopathology 	 3<BR>
*PSY 532 Child Psychopathology 	 3<BR>
*PSY 572 Group Psychotherapy 	 3<BR>
*PSY 503 Methods & Statistics I 	 3<p>

<h3>II. ELECTIVES</h3>

*A T 521 Expressive Arts Workshop 	 3<BR>
*A T 541 Psychodrama in Art Therapy 	 3<BR>
*PSY 565 Objective Measures of Personality 	 3<BR>
*PSY 566 Projective Measures of Personality 	 3<p>

III. PROFESSIONAL CONTRIBUTION (NO CREDIT)<BR>
*A T 555: required of each student at designated time prior to graduation. <p>

*With permission of the Director of Art Therapy and the Art Department 
Chairperson, AT course requirement may be waived and replaced by graduate 
art therapy, psychology, counseling, geriatric or special education courses in 
area of student's interest.<p>

