<h3>Master of Science in Elementary Education</h3>
30 semester hours <br>
This program for ELEMENTARY SCHOOL TEACHERS, who already hold an  
Instructional I Elementary Education Certificate, consists of 30 hours of  
graduate work. The courses are divided into three categories: nine semester  
hours in core courses, which are intended to give the student an  
understanding of research theory, theories of learning and foundations of  
education; twelve semester hours in concentration courses, which provide  
greater depth in general education, greater mastery of an academic field and  
greater proficiency in professional practice, or a combination of these and  
nine semester hours in elective courses, which serve to round out the  
elementary education concentration. <p>
 
<h3>I. CORE COURSES </h3>

9 semester hours <br>
EDUC 501 Research Theory	3 <br>
EDUC 502 Multidisciplinary Foundations of Education 	3 <br>
EDUC 554 Contemporary Learning Theories	3 <br>
EDUC 555 Professional Contribution	0 <p>
 
