12 semester hours  <br>
Twelve additional credits are taken in education or related disciplines,  
depending on the interests and educational background of the student.  
Special programs may be designed to meet individual needs.  <p>

<i>Areas of Concentration: </i><br>
Art Education  <br>
Early Childhood Education  <br>
Instructional Technology  <br>
Reading Education  <br>
Special Education  <br>
Religious Education <p>

<h3>III. ELECTIVES  </h3>

9 semester hours  <br>
Three courses in elective areas may be chosen with the approval of the  
Department Chairperson. <p>

In addition to the successful completion of the course work, the candidate  
must complete a Professional Contribution under the direction of a member of  
the graduate faculty. <p>

