Office.
<P>
<B>Current commuter students who would like to reside on campus
for the Spring semester are asked to</B> stop by the Residence
Life Office, Nazareth Student Center, before 12/13.
<P>
<B>Tutors are asked to</B> stop in at the Academic Excellence
Center, LRC 330, to sign payroll before Thanksgiving break. New
candy supply.
<P>
<center><B>ENTERTAINMENT/CULTURAL EVENTS</B> </center>
<P>
<B>Gallery Walk with WOMEN'S WORK exhibition guest curator Lisa
Hinkle</B>, 11/13, 2 to 3 p.m., Contemporary Gallery, VAC. Ms.
Hinkle will offer insights on the photographs, processes &amp;
artists represented in the exhibition. Free &amp; open to the
public!
<P>
<B>Bus Trip to the Radio City Music Hall to see The Christmas
Show</B>, 11/15, depart Marywood at 2 p.m., return approximately
11:30 p.m., cost is $41 for orchestra seats &amp; $36 for second
mezzanine level seats, price does include cost of bus. If interested,
call Bonnie Alco, 340-6006. Sponsored by the Multi-Cultural Club.
<P>
<B>All Ages Show featuring the local band &quot;juice&quot;</B>,
11/23, 9 p.m. to Midnight, Crystal Room, Nazareth Student Center.
Admission is $1 with valid college I.D. &amp; $3 without college
I.D. Proceeds to benefit the service trip to Peru.
<P>
<B>&quot;WOMEN'S WORK: the art of contemporary female photographers&quot;</B>,
on display now through 11/24 in the Contemporary Gallery, VAC.
This is a powerful exhibition of photographs by major artists
&amp; it's also Marywood's first all-photography exhibit. Gallery
hours are Monday through Wednesday, 9 a.m. to 8 p.m.; Thursday
&amp; Friday, 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.; Saturday &amp; Sunday, 1 to 4
p.m.
<P>
<center><B>OTHER</B> </center>
<P>
<U><B>Collegiate Volunteers Opportunities:</B></U> 
<P>
--Volunteers needed for a Children's Hour with children from the
Valley View Housing Development on 11/15 &amp; 19, 3:30 to 4:30
p.m.;<BR>
--Volunteers needed for survey distribution of residents in the
Mulberry High-Rise, days &amp; hours flexible;<BR>
--Volunteers needed to help implement an HIV/AIDS youth group
with the Lackawanna County AIDS Council, days &amp; hours vary;
<BR>
--Volunteers needed to assist the Steamtown Volunteer Association
with daily operation of its book store &amp; association at the
Steamtown National Historic Site, days &amp; hours flexible;<BR>
--Volunteers needed for various duties at the Green Ridge Nursing
Home, Scranton, including visiting &amp; transporting residents,
decorating &amp; activities, days &amp; hours flexible.
<P>
If interested in any of the above, call or stop by the Collegiate
Volunteers Office, Regina Hall, 348-6211.
<P>
<B>Best Buddies Informational meeting</B>, today, 9 p.m., Gunster
Student Center, University of Scranton campus. Sign up outside
of the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina Hall, or meet in the
Pink Lounge, Nazareth Student Center, on that day. You must attend
meeting to participate in Best Buddies. For further information,
call 348-6211, ext. 2419.
