9 p.m., Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student Center. Agenda: Opportunities
available with teenagers in Scranton area on &amp; off-campus.
<P>
<B>Pink Bunnies Need Not Apply (The Marywood Photography Club)
meeting</B>, 11/18, 9 p.m., VAC 103. Agenda: Members are to bring
photographs taken with disposable cameras.
<P>
<center><B>DEPARTMENT NOTES</B> </center>
<P>
<B>All junior Nutrition &amp; Dietetics students interested in
applying for an American Dietetic Association Scholarship for
the '97-'98 academic year are asked to</B> report to LAC 224 on
11/18 at 2 p.m.
<P>
<B>The last day on which it will be possible to withdraw from
an undergraduate or graduate Fall class is 11/15.</B> The student
must present the completed withdrawal form at the Academic Records
Office, LAC, by 4:30 p.m.
<P>
<B>Registration for the Spring, '97</B>, semester will continue
today for the Class of '99.
<P>
<B>Any Education majors looking for experience in their field
or for Sophomore screening</B> may stop by or call the Collegiate
Volunteers Office, Regina Hall, 348-6211, ext. 2419. Opportunities
exist with children, daycares, tutoring &amp; much more.
<P>
