<P>
<B>Pick A Paper Pumpkin</B>, $1 each, proceeds benefit the March
Of Dimes. Purchase your paper pumpkin in the Collegiate Volunteers
Office, Regina Hall.
<P>
<B>Holiday Food Drive! </B>Monetary &amp; non-perishable donations
now being accepted in the Collegiate Volunteers Office, Regina
Hall.
<P>
<B>A Big Brothers/Big Sisters representative will speak on</B>
11/18 at 9 p.m. in the Blue Lounge, Nazareth Student Center. Topic
will be opportunities available for college students.
<P>
<B>Posters, cards, mugs, etc., are being sold for the Volunteers
In Action fund-raiser.</B> Order forms available today in the
Pink Lounge, Nazareth Student Center, or, any day in the Collegiate
Volunteers Office, Regina Hall. Orders due by 11/15. Decorate
your room!
<P>
<B>&quot;The Creative Project&quot;</B>, 1/25, 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.,
Crystal Room, Nazareth Student Center. This is a fun, inter-active
leadership program presented by Dave Binder. Registration fee
is $3 per person &amp; includes lunch. Space is limited! Sign
up by 12/9 in the Student Activities &amp; Leadership Office,
Nazareth Student Center, or the Collegiate Volunteers Office,
Regina Hall. Open to all students! Sponsored by Marywood College
&amp; the University of Scranton.
<P>
<B>Residents Christmas Dinner sign up will be held in </B>the
Pink Lounge during lunch, 11 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. &amp; dinner, 4:30
to 6 p.m., hours, as follows: 11/18, resident &amp; commuter seniors;
11/19, juniors; 11/20, sophomores; 11/21, freshmen; 11/22, sign
up for all those who wish to go but missed their original sign-up
date.
<P>
<B>&quot;Learning &amp; Assessment&quot;, new student seminar</B>,
11/15, 3 p.m., Academic Excellence Center, LRC 330. The 11/14
seminar is canceled.
<P>
<B>Starving Artists Sale</B>, 11/19, 11 a.m. to 7 p.m., Blue Lounge,
Nazareth Student Center. Prices range from $2 to $50. Wide variety
of undergraduate &amp; graduate student artwork.
<P>
<B>Consult about writing assignments at</B> the Academic Excellence
Center, LRC 330, as follows: Tuesday through Thursday, 10 to 11:30
a.m. &amp; 1 to 8 p.m.; Monday, 10 to 11:30 a.m. &amp; 1 to 4
p.m.
<P>
<center><B>CAREER INFORMATION</B> </center>
<P>
<B>Klatzkin &amp; Co., one of the largest C.P.A. firms in the
Mercer, Burlington &amp; Bucks County areas, would like to review
resumes of Accounting students graduating in the Spring of '97.
</B>Interested students should bring a resume to the Career Services
Office, Nazareth Student Center, no later than 11/15.
<P>
<center><B>SPORTS</B> </center>
