Tournament; 12/12, 4 v. 4 Indoor Wiffleball Tournament &amp; 4
v. 4 Volleyball Tournament. Sign up in the H&amp;PE Center.
<P>
<center><B>FYI</B> </center>
<P>
<B>The front entrance to the Regina Hall Chapel &amp; Campus Ministry
Offices </B>is open Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.
Weekends upon request.
<P>
<B>Commuters are asked to print their suggestions, comments &amp;
concerns that are of interest to commuters &amp; place them in
the Suggestion Boxes that are located as follows: </B>In the vending
area in the HSC; in the Student Lounge in the CNHS; outside of
the entrance of The Woods &amp; in the Pink Lounge, both in the
Nazareth Student Center; &amp; outside of the First Stop in the
LAC. Sponsored by the Student Activities &amp; Leadership Development
Office.
<P>
<B>Current commuter students who would like to reside on campus
for the Spring semester are asked to</B> stop by the Residence
Life Office, Nazareth Student Center, before 12/13.
<P>
<B>Tutors are asked to</B> stop in at the Academic Excellence
Center, LRC 330, to sign payroll before Thanksgiving break. New
candy supply.
<P>
<B>Any senior interested in co-chairing the Senior Gift Campaign
or joining the committee are asked to</B> attend the Class of
'97 meeting scheduled for 11/14 at 9 p.m. in the Blue Lounge,
Nazareth Student Center, or leave a message for Lisa or Veronica
in the Class of '97 mailbox in the Nazareth Student Center.
<P>
<B>Seniors are advised that there is a tentative graduation list
for January, '97, posted on</B> the Undergraduate Dean's enclosed
bulletin board located in the LAC's first floor stairwell between
the LAC &amp; Regina Hall. Check for appropriate degree, correct
name spelling &amp; designated hometown. Any questions or concerns
should be reported to the Dean's Office, LAC 101, by 4:30 p.m.
on 12/6.
<P>
<B>LRC Thanksgiving Break Schedule:</B> 11/26, 8 a.m. to 10 p.m.;
11/27, 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.; 11/28, 29 &amp; 30, closed; 12/1,
1 to 10 p.m.
<P>
<B>The Campus Ministry Office needs 50 employee volunteers who
would be willing to</B> take speaking parts or perform an action
at the Thanksgiving Prayer Breakfast on 11/26 at 7:30 p.m. If
interested, call Sr. Maureen, 348-6211, ext. 4703.
<P>
<B>In appreciation for community involvement,</B> K-Mart is offering
a 10% sale off all regular-priced, &amp;, an extra 10% off sale-priced,
general merchandise on 11/15 &amp; 16.
<P>
<B>The United Way Campaign is in its closing days. </B>If you
have not returned your pledge card yet, please consider sending
your contribution today. If you have already made a pledge or
contribution, thank you for your generosity.
<P>
<B>English majors needed to tutor at</B> the Academic Excellence
Center's Writing Center, LRC 330, for Spring, '97. New hours will
be 1 to 3 p.m. &amp; 8 to 10 p.m., Monday through Thursday &amp;
Sunday, 7 to 10 p.m. Paid position. Blocks of time can be shared.
Stop by the Academic Excellence Center, LRC 330, to inquire.
<P>
<B>Recreation Center Thanksgiving Break Hours: </B>11/27, open
till 8 p.m.; 11/28, 29, 30 &amp; 12/1, closed; 12/2, will re-open
with regular hours.
