<center><B>CAREER INFORMATION</B> </center>
<P>
<B>The School District of Philadelphia on campus 12/4</B> to recruit
graduating Elementary Education &amp; Secondary Education majors.
If interested, come to the Career Services Office, Nazareth Student
Center, to sign up for an interview no later than 11/22. Credential
files &amp; resumes must also be completed by 11/22.
<P>
<B>Career Research Intern position available in the Career Services
Office, Nazareth Student Center, for the Spring semester only.
</B>Six credits of graduate tuition may be obtained for 12 hours
of work per week. No stipend. Duties will involve research, input
&amp; analysis of statistical data. Skills should include computer
experience with Windows &amp; Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Access
&amp; Powerpoint). Please inquire in the Career Services Office,
Nazareth Student Center.
<P>
<B>A cost of living index for major cities in the U.S. is available</B>
in the Career Services Office, Nazareth Student Center.
<P>
<B>Students interested in employment with QVC are asked to</B>
inquire in the Career Services Office, Nazareth Student Center,
before 11/20. Marywood was selected as a top-choice institution
for recruiting by QVC, the world's leader in the electronic retail
industry. They are based in West Chester, PA.
<P>
<B>E.D.S. (Electronic Data Systems), Herndon, VA, is hiring computer
personnel &amp; will review resumes referred by Marywood.</B>
