<html>
<head>
<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  Introduction</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>
<img src="../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt=""><img 
src="../Graphics/about_us.gif" alt="About Us"><br>
Introduction</h1>

On November 10, 1845 a young Belgian priest and three young women met in 
Monroe, Michigan, near Detroit to begin an endeavor whose far reaching 
effects they could little imagine.  The priest, Father Louis Florent 
Gillet, had come to Michigan in 1843.  He saw many needs in his mission 
parish which extended as far away as 60 miles in some directions.  His 
parishioners who were composed of French-Canadians, Irish, and Germans 
suffered a great deal from alcoholism.  He believed that education was 
the key to helping the people whom he served to reach their human 
potential.  To that end he recruited Theresa Maxis Duchemin (co-founder) 
and two other young women to found a religious community of sisters and 
establish a school.
<P>                                                                      
Today, 150 years later, this community is known as the Congregation of 
the Sisters, Servants of the Immaculate Heart of Mary -- or more 
familiarly, as the IHMs.  It consists of three autonomous branches 
centered in Monroe, MI; Philadelphia, PA; and Scranton, PA with a 
combined membership near 3000.  They serve in more than 300 schools, 
including three Congregation-sponsored colleges, as well as serving in the 
fields of medicine, social work, and pastoral care in the United States 
and in many countries around the world.
<P>
The IHMs have touched the lives of many in their rich and vibrant 
history and their story is one that deserves to be told.  Both founders 
encountered great difficulties in their efforts to live out the mission 
to which they believed they were called.  Their struggles against false 
accusation, racial prejudice, gender issues, politics, and 
misunderstanding are the same issues encountered by contemporary 
followers of vision.
<P>
It is unfortunate that today's society has little understanding and many 
misconceptions about the lifestyle choice of religious sisterhood.  The 
portrait painted in popular media is often demeaning and seldom 
accurate.  Few people understand what it is about or why someone would 
choose to live this kind of life.
<P>
This presentation, About Us:  The Congregation of the Sisters, Servants 
of the Immaculate Heart of Mary, Scranton, PA, will tell something of 
the story of the Scranton branch of the IHMs.  In the spirit of the 1995 
celebration of the IHM Sesquicentennial Year, it will celebrate the 
past, illuminate the present, and attempt to give a glimpse of vision 
for the future.  
<P>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<a href="../about-us.html">Return to About Us Home Page</a><br>
