<html>
<head>
<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  IHM Past:  Father Louis Florent Gillet</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>
<img src="../../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt=""><img 
src="../../Graphics/louis_gillet.gif" alt="Louis Florent Gillet"></h2><br>
This presentation about the life of Father Louis Florent Gillet, C.Ss.R., 
is largely excerpted from <cite>Gift of Fire:  Louis Florent 
Gillet -- 1813 - 1892: Christian, Redemptorist, Missionary, 
Cistercian</cite> which was compiled and edited by the IHM Archives Staff 
in Monroe, Michigan and was published on November 14, 1992 to mark the 
hundredth anniversary of his death.
<P><h3>
<img align= middle src="../../Photos/sm_gillet.gif" alt="">
Points in Time -- Chronology of Louis Gillet</h3><br>
Rarely does a human life flow undisturbed between its two points in 
time.  For most, there are intersections, turnings, beyond which life 
continues with different meanings and rhythms.  Each new phase draws 
energy and collective wisdom from the past, channeling it forward with 
new vision and courage.  So it was for Louis Florent Gillet:  <a 
href="gillet2.html">Christian</a>, <a href="gillet3.html">Redemptorist</a>, 
<a href="gillet4.html">Missionary Priest</a> and finally, <a 
href="gillet5.html">Cistercian Contemplative</a>. 
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<a href="gillet2.html">Go to next section</a><br>
<a href="../../about-us.html">Return to About Us Menu</a><br>
<a href="../../index.html">Return to IHM Web Home Page</a>
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
Reference
<P>
IHM Archives Staff (1992).  <cite>Gift of Fire:  Louis Florent Gillet -- 
1813 - 1892:  Christian, Redemptorist, Missionary, Cistercian</cite>.  
Monroe, MI:  St. Mary Convent.
