<h2>
<a name="politicians">Politicians</a></h2>
<P>
<dl>
<dt>Joseph Biden -- U.S. Senator from Delaware
<dd>Attended St. Paul School in Scranton, Pennsylvania.
<P>
<dt>Richard Caliguiri -- former mayor of Pittsburgh, PA
<dd>Attended St. Rosalia School in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.
<P>
<dt><a href="../Photos/casey.gif"><img src="../Photos/casey-th.gif" 
alt="[Picture of Mr. & Mrs. Casey]">Robert Casey</a> -- former governor of 
Pennsylvania
<dd>His wife is a graduate of Marywood college.  His children attended St. 
Clare and St. Paul Schools in Scranton.  He and Mrs. Casey are honorary 
chairpersons of the 1995 IHM Sesquicentennial.
<P>
<dt>James P. Connors -- Mayor of Scranton, PA
<dd>Nephew of Sr. Patrice Conlon.  Attended CCD classes taught by IHMs at 
St. Joseph's in Minooka, PA.
<P>
<dt>Joseph Hannon -- former mayor of Avoca, PA
<dd>Attended St. Mary School in Avoca.
<P>
<dt>Eugene Hickey -- former mayor of Scranton, Pennsylvania
<dd>Brother of Sr. Felice Hickey.
<P>
<dt>James B. McNulty -- former mayor of Scranton, PA
<dd>Nephew of Sr. Regina Barrett.  Cousin of Sr. Adrian Barrett.
<P>
<dt>Edmund Muskee -- former U.S. Senator from Minnesota
<dd>His children attended Little Flower School in Bethesda, Maryland.
<P>
<dt>James Walsh -- Judge and former mayor of Scranton, Pennsylvania
<dd>Attended St. Patrick School in Scranton.  His children also attended St. 
Patrick's. Nephew of Sr. Dominica Gurrell and Sr. Pancratius Walsh.
<P>
<dt>Acie Ward, J. D. -- first woman and first African-American elected as 
Assistant Attorney General in North Carolina
<dd>Attended St. Joseph in New Bern, NC and Marywood College in Scranton.
<P>
</dl>
