<html>
<head>
<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  IHM Future:  IHM Directions</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>
<img src="../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt=""><img 
src="../Graphics/ihm_direction.gif" alt="IHM Directions"></h1>
<P>
In July, 1994, the General Chapter of the Sisters, Servants of the 
Immaculate Heart of Mary, Scranton, Pennsylvania, met to map out a 
direction for the Congregation as it moves into the twenty-first 
century.  What follows are the Reaffirmation of Corporate Identity, 
Corporate Commitment and Strategies for futhering the commitment adopted 
by that body. <P>
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
          ____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<center>
<h1>Acts of Chapter<br>
July 1994</h1>
</center>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<center>| <a href="#identity">Corporate Identity</a> | <a 
href="#commitment">Corporate Commitment</a> | <a 
href="#strategies">Strategies</a> |</center>
<P> 
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
          ____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<center>
<a name="identity">
<h2>Reaffirmation of IHM Corporate Identity</h2></a>
Our mission as Sisters, Servants of the <br>
Immaculate Heart of Mary, Scranton, <br>
Pennsylvania, is to follow Jesus as a <br>
community of disciples, aware that we are <br>
sent to be a clear and understandable <br>
<strong>Prophetic Witness</strong><br>
to the presence of God in the world.
</center>
<P>
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
          ____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<center>
<a name="commitment">
<h2>IHM Corporate Commitment<br>
1994 - 1998</h2></a>
As a congregation, as local<br>
communities and as individuals, we<br>
commit ourselves to work toward <br>
dignity and justice for all creation by<br>
empowering women and by addressing<br>
structures which are at the root of<br>
women's oppression.
</center>
<P>
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
          ____________________________________________________________________">
<P><h2>
<a name="strategies">Strategies:</a></h2>
<P>
<ol>
<li><a href="#1">Education on Gender Bias and Women's Issues</a>
<li><a href="#2">Covenant Relationships</a>
<li><a href="#3">Advocacy and Systemic Change</a>
<li><a href="#4">Theresa's Treasure</a>
<li><a href="#5">Peace Site</a>
<li><a href="#6">Technology</a>
</ol>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h2><a name="1">Strategy 1</a><br>
Education on Gender Bias and Women's Issues</h2>
<ul>
<li>Create a multimodal process in which each sister will make a 
commitment to learn and to share perspective and experiences about 
gender bias and empowerment of women.
<P>
<li>Gather and disseminate information/resource materials, suitable for 
all ministries, that will address women's issues.
<P>
</ul>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h2><a name="2">Strategy 2</a><br>
Covenant Relationships</h2>
Increase awareness and knowledge of our sisters' diversified ministries 
by yearly covenants - sister to sister or local community to sister - to 
support one another's ministries in any way possible.  This relationship 
will result in greater inclusivity, more common ownership of our 
ministries, greater collaboration, and evangelization of and by one another.
<P>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h2><a name="3">Strategy 3</a><br>
Advocacy and Systemic Change</h2>
Utilize and expand use of existing resources and technology (e.g. 
Marywood College, St. Joseph Center, Marian Community Hospital, IHM 
Spiritual Renewal Center, Our Lady of Grace Center, Congregation 
committees, collaborative networks, action circles, justice gatherings, 
women's resource centers, IHM Peace and Justice Center, etc.) to enable 
each sister and others with whom we collaborate to become educated 
advocates for systemic change of unjust structures or situations.
<P>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h2><a name="4">Strategy 4</a><br>
Theresa's Treasure</h2>
Lend financial support to women's causes by:
<ul>
<li>choosing to invest some available monies from the IHM Charitable 
Trust into socially responsible investments that directly help women.
<P>
<li>encouraging individual sisters and local communities to contribute 
to Congregational funds that will provide seed money for women's projects.
<P>
</ul>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h2><a name="5">Strategy 5</a><br>
Peace Site</h2>
Each sister within the Congregation has the call to be a Peace Site.  In 
addition, every local community and thus the Congregation has the same 
call.  The extension of the concept can become a reality as each one 
focuses on women's issues with a nonviolent stance.  Then each exudes 
Christ's power to all.
<P>
Recommended ways for individual sisters and local communities to link 
the Peace Site concept to women's issues include:
<P>
<ul>
<li>making a commitment to faith sharing on a local community level
<P>
<li>inviting other women to faith sharing on a local community level
<P>
<li>inviting persons from local resource centers to assist with education of 
IHM membership on women's issues
<P>
<li>taking action for justice to empower women
<P>
<li>evaluating yearly each sister's and local community's commitment to 
women's issues.
<P>
</ul>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h2><a name="6">Strategy 6</a><br>
Technology</h2>
Initiate steps in the IHM Communications Office to receive and 
disseminate information through the use of E-mail and the Internet.  
Such action will mobilize efforts to further Congregational action steps 
and strategies.
<P>
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
          ____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<a href="../about-us.html">Return to About Us Menu</a><br>
<a href="../index.html">Return to IHM Web Home Page</a>
<P>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
