<CENTER><h1>
<img src="../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt="IHM Web"><img 
src="../Graphics/cresco.gif" alt=""></h1></CENTER><br>
<h1>IHM Spiritual Renewal Center Calendar of Events</h1>
<i>IHM Spiritual Renewal Center -- Box 568, RR 1, Cresco, PA  18326-- (717) 
595-7548<br>
The IHM Spiritual Renewal Center is located in a peaceful setting in 
the heart of the Pocono Mountains of Northeast Pennsylvania.  
Hermitage, private and directed retreats are available.  The Center 
has accommodations for groups of 15 overnight guests and can 
accommodate 35 for a day program.</i> 
<P> 
<h2><a href="hermitage.html">Hermitages Available</a></h2> 
<H2>1997<br>
</H2>
<h2>| <a href="#january">January</a> | <a href="#february">February</a> | <a href="#march">March</a> | <a href="#april">April</a> | <a href="#may">May</a> |</h2> 
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
__________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<h2><a name="january">January</a></h2>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<dl>
<DT><H3>10 - 12 / Friday - Sunday</H3>
<DD><b>DeMello Weekend Retreat</b><BR>
Anthony DeMello, SJ was an expert in teaching us how to be aware of God in the ordinary events of our life.  This weekend will focus on the prayer experience that DeMello left to us to help enrich our lives by being cognizant of how God is found in everyday happenings.<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Arrive:  Friday -- 7:00 p.m.
<LI>Depart:  Sunday -- 10:30 a.m.
</UL>

<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>22 / Wednesday</H3>
<DD><b>Prayer/Leisure Day</b><BR>
This days provide time for participants to rest, relax, pray and be renewed in body and spirit.<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.

</dl>
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
__________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<a href="#top"><img align=right src="../Graphics/up.gif" alt="[Go up]"></a>
<h2><a name="february">February</a></h2>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<dl>
<DT><H3>8 / Saturday</H3>
<DD><b>Living Into Loving</b><BR>
This day of reflection and prayer will use the material introduced in the July workshops by Fr. Paul Wadell and Sr. Carole Riley.  It will give participants an opportunity to pray, discuss and process the ideas and values presented in the summer sessions to see how they relate to their lives.<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>13 / Thursday</H3>
<DD><b>Lenten Evening of Prayer</b><BR>
An evening of Scriptural Prayer which will help to enrich your Lenten journey and prepare you for a more intense participation in the Sunday Lenten Liturgy<BR>
7:15 - 8:30 p.m.
<br>
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>18 / Tuesday</H3>
<DD><B>Lenten Day of Prayer</B><BR>
Lent is a special time to renew our commitment to God.  Begin Lent with a day of prayer.  Take time to focus on your relationship with God and see what you can do during Lent to enhance that relationship.<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.<BR>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>20 / Thursday</H3>
<DD><b>Lenten Evening of Prayer</b><BR>
An evening of Scriptural Prayer which will help to enrich your Lenten journey and prepare you for a more intense participation in the Sunday Lenten Liturgy<BR>
7:15 - 8:30 p.m.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>23 - 28 / Sunday - Friday</H3>
<DD><b>Winter Retreat</b><BR>
This retreat will offer participants an opportunity to balance the active life with contemplative prayer by focusing on Gospel values.<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Arrive:  Sunday -- 2:00 p.m.
<LI>Depart:  Friday -- 2:00 p.m.
</UL>


</dl>
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
__________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<a href="#top"><img align=right src="../Graphics/up.gif" alt="[Go up]"></a>
<h2><a name="march">March</a></h2>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<dl>
<DT><H3>6 / Thursday</H3>
<DD><b>Lenten Evening of Prayer</b><BR>
An evening of Scriptural Prayer which will help to enrich your Lenten journey and prepare you for a more intense participation in the Sunday Lenten Liturgy<BR>
7:15 - 8:30 p.m.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>7 / Friday</H3>
<DD><b>Associates/Volunteers Prayer Day</b><BR>
Volunteers, prayer associates and former IHMs are invited to spend a day in prayer, sharing and mutual support.  This is a special time for members to become acquainted with each other.<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>11 / Tuesday</H3>
<DD><b>Friendship:  Food for the Journey</b><BR>
A day of prayer that will explore the different hungers in our lives:  our need to be known, heard, understood, taken seriously, chosen and loved.<BR>
Conducted by Sr. Kathryn Clauss, IHM<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.

<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>13 / Thursday</H3>
<DD><b>Lenten Evening of Prayer</b><BR>
An evening of Scriptural Prayer which will help to enrich your Lenten journey and prepare you for a more intense participation in the Sunday Lenten Liturgy<BR>
7:15 - 8:30 p.m.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>15 / Saturday</H3>
<DD><b>Healing and Reconciliation</b><BR>
A Lenten day of prayer that will examine prayerful ways of becoming aware of those areas in our lives in need of healing and reconciliation.<BR>
Facilitator:  Sr. Redempta Sweeney, IHM<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.

<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>20 / Thursday</H3>
<DD><b>Lenten Evening of Prayer</b><BR>
An evening of Scriptural Prayer which will help to enrich your Lenten journey and prepare you for a more intense participation in the Sunday Lenten Liturgy<BR>
7:15 - 8:30 p.m.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>23 - 30 / Sunday - Sunday</H3>
<DD><b>Holy Week Retreat</b><BR>
Jesus calls us to a deeper union each day of our lives.  Spend Holy Week in silence and prayer preparing for the greatest feast of the Church year.<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Arrive:  Sunday, March 23 -- 7:00 p.m.
<LI>Depart:  Sunday, March 30 -- 10:00 a.m.
</UL>
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>27 - 30 / Thursday - Sunday</H3>
<DD><b>Pascal Triduum Retreat</b><BR>
This retreat will be highlighted by the liturgical services conducted by Father Berard McTierney, CP.  The atmosphere of prayer and silence will facilitate your entrance into the Pascal mystery.<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Arrive:  Thursday -- 1:00 p.m.
<LI>Depart:  Sunday -- 10:00 a.m.
</UL>

</dl>
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
__________________________________________________________________">
