<h2><a name="april">April</a></h2>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<dl>
<DT><H3>4 - 5 / Friday - Sunday</H3>
<DD><b>Silver Jubilarian Prayer/Celebration Days</b><BR>
A time for IHM Jubilarians to renew and refresh themselves spiritually and socially by spending time with God and with each other.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>16 / Wednesday</H3>
<DD><b>Prayer/Leisure Day</b><BR>
This days provide time for participants to rest, relax, pray and be renewed in body and spirit.<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>22 / Tuesday</H3>
<DD><b>Secretary's Prayer/Leisure Day</b><BR>
Because she spends most of her time in an office with constant activity, your secretary will appreciate your thoughtfulness in giving her time to be renewed in body and spirit.  A day of reflection and interaction with her peers will be a welcome gift for any secretary.  Lunch will be provided.<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.

</dl>
<img src="../Lines/sb10.gif" 
alt= 
" ____________________________________________________________________
__________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<a href="#top"><img align=right src="../Graphics/up.gif" alt="[Go up]"></a>
<h2><a name="may">May</a></h2>
<img src="../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<br>
<dl>
<DT><H3>7 / Wednesday</H3>
<DD><b>Mothers' Day of Prayer</b><BR>
Since many mothers are overworked and overextended, a day of quiet, peacefulness and prayer will be a most welcome gift.  This is a gift a mother can give herself or one that you can provide for her.  A special time "to be" will be appreciated by any mother.
<BR>
10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.
<br><img src="../Lines/sb10-2.gif" 
alt="_________________________________________________________">
<br>
<DT><H3>18 - 23 / Sunday - Friday</H3>
<DD><b>Spring Retreat</b><BR>
As nature begins to be renewed, nurture the new life that is being renewed within you.  Spend these days in quiet communion with the God of springtime.  This five day retreat can be directed or private.<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Arrive:  Sunday -- 4:00 p.m.
<LI>Depart:  Friday -- 1:00 p.m.
</UL>

</dl>
