<html>
<head>
<!-- Thanks for looking at our Web page.
     Please let us know how we can improve our site. -->

<title>Marywood College Business Programs</title>
</head>

<body background="/images/backgrnd.gif">
<img src="/images/mwlogos.jpg" align=left hspace=10>
<h1>Marywood College</h1>
<h2>Business Programs</h2>
<br clear=left><hr>

<pre>
	<h3><a href="#programs">Business Programs</a></h3>
	I.	<a href="#accounting">Accounting</a><br>
	II.	<a href="#busadmin">Business Administration</a>, concentration:<br>
			<a href="#planning">Financial Planning</a><br>
			<a href="#marketing">Marketing</a><br>
			<a href="#management">Management</a><br>
	III.	<a href="#cis">Computer Information and Telecommunication Systems</a><br>
	IV.	<a href="#ib">International Business</a><br>
</pre>

<hr>
<h3><a name="programs">Business Programs</a></h3>
The Marywood College business programs are designed to prepare students for supervisory and 
administrative positions where a high degree of managerial and/or technical expertise will be required, 
and are open to high school graduates with either academic of business backgrounds.  Through the 
various majors offered, Marywood's Business programs can help you develop your career objectives.<p>

<h3><a name="accounting">Accounting</a></h3>
Are you interested in becoming a member of one of the fastest growing professions today -- one which 
forecasts a major growth rate?  If so, consider a career in a consulting practice...public...corporate or 
government accounting.  Marywood offers a well-rounded education with a strong background in liberal 
arts so necessary for success in the accounting profession.<p>

<h3><a name="busadmin">Business Administration</a></h3>
This is one of the most popular areas of study for college students because of the many career 
opportunities for which they can be prepared.  Students in this major are provided with tools needed for 
work as administrators in a variety of organizations covering private and public sectors.  Three 
functional areas of business are integrated into the Business Administration program.  Based upon the 
student's career goals and personal interests, and with guidance of an academic advisor, majors can select 
Finance Planning, Marketing, or Management as an area of concentration.<p>

<h3><a name="planning">Financial Planning</a></h3>
The Finance area of concentration prepares students for career opportunities in financial management that 
are both challenging and rewarding.  The study of finance blends concepts from Accounting, Economics 
and Statistics into the course work composed of Investment and Portfolio Management, Personal Financial 
Planning, Money and Banking, Financial Management, Advanced Topics in Financial Planning, etc.  
Students selecting this area of concentration must complete 18 hours in Finance, which could include a 
course or two in insurance, real estate or an internship in investment banking or corporate financial 
planning.<p>

<h3><a name="marketing">Marketing</a></h3>
As we move from a "production-oriented society" into a "marketing-oriented society," careers in 
marketing are looking more promising than ever.<p>
With emphasis on quality and customer focus, more companies are going to be looking for individuals 
that are able to understand the importance of a well-integrated marketing program.<p>
Here at Marywood College, we prepare you for such a challenge.  Along with the other business 
requirements, we introduce marketing majors to Marketing Research, Marketing Management and 
International Marketing.<p>

<h3><a name="management">Management</a></h3>
Training and skills to prepare managers to contribute to the development of organizational structure, 
staffing requirements and planning and administering employee benefits, as well as handling labor 
relations problems within organizations are part of the preparation majors receive within this functional 
area of specialization.  Through a set of required and elective courses focusing on management and the 
decision-making process relative to administrative theory, students are prepared to enter business 
firm, social agencies and other organizations in the areas of personnel management and human 
relations.<p>

<h3><a name="cis">Computer Information and Telecommunication Systems</a></h3>
The impact of information technology is widespread.  It has radically changed how business is conducted 
and has become a vital component in achieving and maintaining a competitive edge.<p>
Today, leading corporations are using information technology to develop new products and services, edge 
out competition, forge more effective relationships with customers and suppliers and radically change 
their internal operations and organizations.<p>
Here at Marywood College, we prepare you to become proficient in varied aspects of information technology and in the business aspect of organization.<p>

<h3><a name="ib">International Business</a></h3>
Europe 1992 has become a reality and a true Single Market.  Therefore, the significance of global 
marketing, finance and management of international operations is essential to multi-national and 
trans-national organizations.  The Marywood International Business Program prepares the student 
for the multiple career opportunities available in the various sectors of the multi-national corporate 
global operations.  Students majoring in this field are required to complete 45 semester hours in 
business in addition to 21 credits in a foreign language.  Students should spend a semester abroad in 
a country of their choice relative to the language selected in the program.  Through the advice of both 
foreign language faculty and business faculty, the student's academic program is outlined.<p>


<hr>
[<a href="/">Marywood's Home Page</a>] 
[<a href="/websites.htm">Other Places</a>] 
<p>

