<HTML><TITLE>WVMW-FM 91.5</TITLE>
<body background="/images/backgrnd.gif">
<Center><H1>WVMW-FM 91.5</H1></Center>
<Body>
<P>	Welcome to the WVMW homepage.  WVMW-FM is a studuent-run and
student-operated FM radio station operating with 100 watts of power at 91.5
megahertz on the dial by authority of the FCC in Washington, D.C.<Br>
It is located in the Learning Resources Center on the campus of Marywood
College.
<HR>
<CENTER><H2>FORMAT</H2></Center>
<P>	The format here at WVMW (or VMFM as it is sometimes called) is<Br>
varied and eclectic.  Normal progrmming consists of mostly underground<Br>
artist who are not getting airplay on commercial stations.  A random<Br>
sampling of our music library consists of anything from ALL to Ween, and<Br>
all of it is good.  You won't find any Van Halen or Green Day or Pearl Jam<Br>
in our studios.  While we respect those artists, they get plenty of airplay<Br>
on other 'commercial' FM stations.  We are not a commercial station<Br>
(meaning we don't sell advertising time to sponsors) therefore, we don't<Br>
have to play the safe route when it comes to music.  We can be
experimental,<Br>
and the style of the programming can shift with each DJ.  To learn more<Br>
about what is currently in heavy rotation here at VMFM, check out our<Br>
<A HRef="currents.html">"Currents"</A> page.<Br>
<HR>
<CENTER><H2>OTHER "STUFF"</H2></Center>
Alternative programming is not the only thing we offer here at VMFM.<Br>
There are other shows at set times during the day which offer access to<Br>
specific genres that you can't hear on other radio stations.  You can hear<Br>
blues, jazz, 40's and 50's pop music, and improvisational styles of music, as<Br>
well as other shows which are more fun and offer a more irreverent view of<Br>
music's past.  Show's that fall under this category are "Flashback to the 80's"<Br>
and "Marywood Ballroom".  For more info on our shows, times and DJ's<Br> 
check out the <A HRef="schedule.html">"Schedule"</A> page.<Br>
<P>In addition to music, you can hear basketball here on VMFM.  Everytime the
Pacers are at home, tune into VMFM 91.5.  We bring you all the action - live
and in stereo.  Both men's and women's teams are covered, and on occasion, we
have doubleheaders.  If you want to find out when to tune in, check out our
<A HRef="sports.html">"sports"</A> page.<Br>
If you want in depth information about all the stats and other stuff for ALL of
Marywood's sports, <A HRef="pacerpride.html">"Pacer Pride"</A> is the show for
you.  Your hosts, Bill Jones and John Seitzinger bring you news, stats,
interviews and picks relating to Marywood sports, and then some.  From field
hockey in the fall, to baseball in the spring, they keep you updated if you 
can't make it to the games in person.  This show is for the sports nut in all
of us.
 
<P> For more information, questions, or comments, send e-mail to: <Br>
<A HRef="mailto:commarts@ac.marywood.edu"><B>Commarts@ac.marywood.edu</B></A><Br>

<P>This page last updated February 23, 1996<Br>

Copyright 1995. All rights reserved.

</Body>
</HTML>
