<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Welcome to TVM-37</TITLE>
<body background="/images/backgrnd.gif">
<CENTER>
<H1>TVM-37</H1>
<H2>Television, Marywood Style</H2>
</CENTER>                               
</HEAD>
<BOY>
<HR>
<H3> What does TVM-37 stand for?</H3>
Well I could begin to tell you that whole line about how we stand for
commitment to excellence and no mistakes ever, but that would be a line and a
half. TVM-37 simply stands for <B>"TV-Marywood on cable channel 37."</B> We are 
a college station made up of shows produced, directed, created, inspired, and
crewed by Marywood College Students and we are cable-cast  on Verto Cable
 channel 37 Monday thru Thursday from 7PM to 9PM. Follow this link to see the
full TVM-37 <A href="TVMSKED.html">line-up</A>.


<H3>What do we offer?</H3>
Currently at TVM-37 we produce a regular line-up of 7 shows and many special
features. Shows range from instructional (e.g. <A href="GH.html">Over at Grandma's House</A>
and <A href="gs.html">Guitar Shop</A>), to news/sports information
(e.g. <A href="CLoserLook.html">A Closer Look</A> ,<A href="TVN.html">TVM News</A>,and
 <A HRef="pacerpride.html">Pacer Pride</A>),to talkshows (e.g.<A href="TL.html">Twilite</A>  and <A href="NE.html">No Clips</A>).
Special shows include Senior Workshops which are used for filling degree
requirments, community service projects, live basketball games, concerts, and
student projects.
  
<H3>Who does the work and why?</H3>
Almost all the shows that are produced at TVM-37 are totally student run. In 
most cases, students from the department and other departments produce, direct,
