<Head>
<Title>Marywood U.S. Statutes Code Regulations Laws Legislation Congress Senate House of Representatives</Title>
</Head>

<Body Background="bgrnd003.jpg" BGColor=#FFFFFF Text=#000000 Link=#0000FF VLink=#800080 ALink=#FF00FF>


<BGSOUND SRC="ros-barb.mid" LOOP=INFINITE><Br>

<embed src="ros-barb.mid" hidden="true" loop=infinite>



<Center><IMG src="gr_ban01.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><IMG src="redlogo4.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><IMG src="gr_ban01.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Center><IMG src="hline037.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><I><B>"This country has come to feel the same when Congress is in session <Br>as when the baby gets hold of a hammer."</B> </I><Br>Will Rogers</Center> 
<Center><IMG src="hline037.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Center><IMG src="capext.gif" alt="United States Capital GIF"></Center><P>

<H1><Center><I>Federal</I></Center></H1><P>

<H3><I><U>Historic Documents</U></I></H3><P>

<A href="http://lcweb2.loc.gov/const/mdbquery.html" Alt="">The Big Three</A>...The Federalist Papers, the Declaration of Independence, and the Constitution of the United States, brought to you by <I>Thomas.</I> Also other assorted early Congressional documents. Searchable.<P>

<H3><I><U>Codes and Legislation</U></I></H3><P>

<A href="http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/" Alt="">The United States Code</A>...From the Legal Information Institute at Cornell Law School, this is a fully searchable database of Titles 1-50 of the U.S. Code.<P>

<A href="http://law.house.gov/cfr.htm" Alt="">The Code of Federal Regulations</A>...From the House of Representatives Law Library, a searchable database of the CFR.  Allows fuzzy searches.<P>


<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://thomas.loc.gov" Alt="">Legislation, Passed & Pending</A>  
<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> From <I>Thomas</I>; the floor activities, pending bills, Congressional Record, and committee information of the 104th (current) Congress.  Searchable by a variety of ways and means, including keyword/phrase, index term, bill/amendment number, stage in legislative process, sponsor/co-sponsor, or committee. This site is assuredly an example of tax dollars wisely invested.<P>

<H3><I><U>The Congress</U></I></H3><P>

<A href="http://www.senate.gov/" Alt="">The U.S. Senate</A>...A directory of Senators with links to their home pages and e-mail addresses.  A guide to Senate committees, a virtual tour of the Capitol Building, and more.<P>

<A href="http://www.house.gov/Welcome.html" Alt="">The U.S. House of Representatives</A>...A committee directory, an index of Representatives with e-mail links, schedules for legislative activity, and listings on how particular Representatives voted on specific bills, etc.<P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://law.house.gov/1.htm" Alt="">The House Law Library</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> U.S. Federal and State laws; U.S. treaties; International Law and laws of other nations. Attorney and legal professional directories.<P>

<H1><Center><I>State</I></Center></H1><P>

<A href="http://lawlib.wuacc.edu/washlaw/uslaw/statelaw.html" Alt="">State Law Locator</A>...From the Washburn University School of Law Library, a directory to state law and state law related websites.  Great search options.<P>

<A href="http://law.house.gov/17.htm" Alt="">U.S. State and Territorial Laws</A>...From the House Law Library. Similar to the Washburn site, what's available depends upon what the particular states listed have put on the Web.<P>

<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><B><I>"Congress is so strange. A man gets up to speak and says nothing.<Br>Nobody listens -- and then everybody disagrees."</I></B><Br>Boris Marshalov</Center>
<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<IMG align=center src="eye_bar.gif" alt=""><BR>

