<Center><IMG src="gr_ban01.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><IMG src="redlogo5.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><IMG src="gr_ban01.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Center><IMG src="hline037.gif" alt=""></Center><Br>
<Center><I><B>"The execution of the laws is more important than the making of them."</I><Br> Thomas Jefferson</B></Center><P>
<Center><IMG src="hline037.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Center><I><H1>The Presidency</H1></I></Center><P>

<IMG src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/WH/Welcome.html" Alt="">The White House</A> <IMG src="redstar.gif" alt=""> This site has become an excellent resource under President Clinton's administration. Through the "GovBot" database, you can search and access all 185,002 (and counting) U.S. Government websites.  Along with links to all executive and independent government agencies, all Executive Orders, publicly released White House documents and Presidential addresses of the current administration are also available. On the personal side, there is biographical information on the First Family, and past Presidents, and you can send e-mail to Bill, Hill' or Al.<P>


<Center><B><I>"One man with courage makes a majority."</I></B><Br>Andrew Jackson</Center>

<Center><IMG src="g_links.gif" alt=""></Center><P>
<I><Center><H2>Executive Branch Agencies</H2></Center></I><P>

<A href="http://www.odci.gov/cia/" Alt="">Central Intelligence Agency</A>...All you ever wanted to know about "Langley" (or at least, what they'll tell you).  Actually, their World Factbook and Factbook on Intelligence are great reference works.<P>

<A href="http://www.cpsc.gov" Alt="">Consumer Product Safety Commission</A>...Good safety information, plus a complaints department to report unsafe products.<P>

<A href="http://www.usdoj.gov" Alt="">Department of Justice</A>...Janet Reno's site, you may have some difficulty with downloading this -- Its been rather iffy since the hackers got in.<P>

<A href="http://ustreas.gov" Alt="">Department of the Treasury</A>...From the folks that make the money that you give to the link below below.  Nice graphics of a C-Note, how to detect counterfeit, and a neat "Tours and Treasures" page.<P>

<A href="http://www.irs.ustreas.gov" Alt="">Internal Revenue Service</A>...Lots of helpful information, in a format less grim than might be expected.<P>

<A href="http://www.fbi.gov/homepage.htm" Alt="">Federal Bureau of Investigation</A>...Basic information about the FBI, including their "10 Most Wanted", current investigations, FBI Faqs, and their annual crime reports.<P>

<A href="http://www.ftc.gov" Alt="">Federal Trade Commission</A>...Lots of valuable consumer protection information.<P>

<A href="http://www.lcweb.loc.gov/copyright" Alt="">United States Copyright Office</A>...Copyright basics, registration information, application forms, etc.<P>

<A href="http://www.uspto.gov" Alt="">United States Patent and Trademark Office</A>...Search for US patents, find out about trademark registration of Internet domain names, et al.<P>

<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><B><I>"President means chief servant."</I></B><Br>Mahatma Gandhi</Center>
<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

