<head>
<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  IHM Past:  Brushes with Fame:  Dillinger</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>
<img src="../../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt=""><img 
src="../../Graphics/b_w_fame.gif" alt="Brushes With Fame"></h2><br>
<h2>Dillinger's Hide Out</h2>
John Dillinger was in Pittsburgh and was being followed by the FBI.  He 
came to St. Mary of the Mount Convent and asked for food and a place to 
stay.  The Sister in the kitchen, not knowing who he was, told him he 
had to work so he cleaned the porches and sidewalks for his food and 
accommodations. 
<P>  
One night, Sr. St. Agnes got up to go to the bathroom.  She saw feet 
sticking out from under the curtain in the hallway.  She decided to go 
back into her room and get into bed.  Dillinger followed her into her 
room and, seeing that she was not going to call the police, quietly left 
the convent.
<P>
As soon as he crossed the street, he was arrested by an FBI agent who 
had the convent under surveilance.
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
