<head>
<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  IHM Past:  Brushes with Fame:  Dr. Mudd</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>
<img src="../../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt=""><img 
src="../../Graphics/b_w_fame.gif" alt="Brushes With Fame"></h2><br>
<h2>Dr. Samuel A. Mudd</h2>
Dr. Mudd was the southern Maryland doctor who set John Wilkes Booth's leg 
after President Abraham Lincoln's assassination.  Sentenced to Fort 
Jefferson Prison, Dry Tortugas, Florida, he was pardoned by President 
Andrew Johnson for his medical help in the yellow fever epidemic there.
<P>
The Mudd family is still working to have his name cleared.
<P>
Origin of the phrase:  "Your name will be Mudd."
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
