<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  IHM Future:  It Could Be You!:  Prayer 
Associates</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>
<img src="../../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt="IHM Web:  About Us: "><img 
src="../../Graphics/could_be.gif" alt="It Could Be You!"></h2><br>
<h2>Prayer Associates</h2>
<h3>Partners in Prayer</h3>
The Sisters, Servants of the Immaculate Heart of Mary, Scranton, 
Pennsylvania, invite you to join them in praying for the needs of the 
Church, the Congregation and for each other.
<P>
Membership as a Prayer Associate is available to everyone, with no 
formal commitment other than unity in prayer/service.
<P>
As members of our IHM Congregation we rejoice in the redeeming love of 
Jesus Christ who joins us to himself and to all others in His Church by 
the Power of the Holy Spirit.  Because we share in the redeeming mission 
of Jesus Christ, we join together as partners for mutual encouragement 
and support in living out our gospel commitment.
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
"Again I tell you, if two of you join your voices on earth to pray for 
anything whatever, it shall be granted you by my Father in heaven.  
Where two or three are gathered in my name, there am I in their 
midst." -- Mt 18: 19-20 
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h3>Benefits</h3>
<P>
<ul> 
<li>Daily remembrance in prayers of the Sisters of IHM.
<li>Remembrance in monthly liturgy for the intentions of all of the 
Associates.
<li>Opportunity to participate with the Sisters in days of prayer.
<li>Prayer materials for the seasons of Advent and Lent.
<li>Subscription to JOURNEY, the IHM ministry publication.
</ul>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h3>Participation</h3>
<P>
<ul>
<li>No formal commitment.
<li>Associates are encouraged to pray daily for the Sisters of IHM, for 
their works and for vocations to the Congregation.
<li>Associates are invited to request prayers at any time for their special 
needs or intentions.
<li>Associates are given opportunities for sharing with the Sisters through 
prayer, liturgy and service.
</ul>
<h3>Come! Unite with us in the prayer and mission of the IHM 
Congregation.</h3>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
If interested contact:
<pre>
	              Sr. Katherine Sugrue, IHM
            	      IHM Center - Marywood
          	      Scranton, PA  18509

          	      (717) 346-5411
</pre>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
