<head>
<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  IHM Future:  It Could Be You!:  Volunteer 
Associates</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>
<img src="../../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt="IHM Web:  About Us: "><img 
src="../../Graphics/could_be.gif" alt="It Could Be You!"></h2><br>
<h2>IHM Volunteer Associate Program</h2>
<h3>Like an adventure...?</h3>
Willing to risk a few weeks or even a year of your life?<br>
Brave enough to step away from the crowd...?<br>
Daring enough to reach out and touch another's life...?
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h3>Goal:</h3>
This program provides men and women volunteers an opportunity to share 
in the work of the IHM Sisters in areas of education, business, health 
care, social services, pastoral, spiritual and support services.
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h3>Objectives:</h3>
<P>
<ol>
<li>To recruit, orientate and support volunteers to work with IHM Sisters in 
parishes, schools, health care facilities and programs of family 
support, especially for poor children and their families.
<P>
<li>To deepen the spirituality of volunteers through personal and communal 
prayer and the experience of working and sharing with women religious.
<P>
<li>To develop models of volunteer involvement in the active ministry of the 
Church.
</ol>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h3>Methodology:</h3>
The program utilizes the "immersion" method.  After careful 
consideration, evaluation and prayerful reflection, the volunteers are 
placed as soon as possible into work experiences.  This program is a 
volunteer partnership to further the work of the Church and of the IHM 
Congregation.
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h3>Requirements:</h3>
Volunteers without dependents, who love the poor, are open to growth and 
adventure and want to share in a faith community experience while 
serving the people of God.  The program is flexible; volunteers usually 
make a commitment fo two weeks to two years.
<P>
Age:	21 years or older; (18 years - Summer Program)
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h3>Benefits:</h3>
<P>
<ul>
<li>Room and board
<li>stipend
<li>insurance (year commitment)
<li>the experience of a lifetime with a guarantee that you will get more 
out of it than it will get out of you.
</ul>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
<h3>Locations:</h3>
<pre>
	New York	North Carolina		Maryland
	New Jersey      Connecticut          	Pennsylvania
	Delaware	Washington, DC    	Mississippi
</pre>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
"There is a variety of gifts but always the same Spirit; there are all 
sorts of Service to be done, but always to the same Lord; working in all 
sorts of different ways in different people; it is working in all of 
them."	-- 1 Cor 12:4-7
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
If Interested, Contact:
<pre>
		Sr. Katherine Sugrue, IHM
		IHM Center - Marywood
		Scranton, PA  18509

		(717) 346-5411
</pre>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
