<HTML><Title>Sports Coverage</Title>
<body background="/images/backgrnd.gif">
<Center>Sports on the Radio</Center>
<Body>
<P>At VMFM, we don't just play music, we carry every home basketball game, for
both the Pacers and Lady Pacers here at Marywood, live as it is happening.  Our
on-air sports team is the best of any college in the area.  Hear the excitement
live on VMFM 91.5!!!<Br>

<Center><B>Upcoming Schedule</B></Center><Br>
<B>1995-96 season completed</B><Br>
<Br>
<P>* - The 1995-96 basketball season has been completed here at Marywood
College.  Tune in next season to see if the young Pacer squad can challenge for
a PAC playoff spot and if the Lady Pacers can advance past the first round.<Br>

<Center>On air personalities for 1995-1996 season</Center>
<P>Carol Dean - Ms. Dean brings a wealth of experience after being a sports
reporter for the local CBS-TV affiliate (WYOU Ch. 22), and she uses it to her
advantage as one of the few female sportscasters in our area.<Br>

<P>Frank Coccuza - A newcomer here to the VMFM Sports team, he has a style all
his own.  An insider with the athletic department, he gets personal and
informative interviews with the all the team members, from the head coach
right down to the 15th player.<Br>

<P>Bill Jones - A member of the men's baskteball team, Bill obviously comes to
us on a limited basis.  But if it is a women's game, watch out Dick Vitale! 
Bill knows more about all the players than anyone else out there.  Also a
co-host and co-producer of <B>Pacer Pride</B>, sports is the name of his
game.<Br>

<P>Jared Rivera - Quick-paced action and a love for the game mark Mr. Rivera's
style.  Three years of experience and a good general knowledge of the game
have helped him become the most active of the group.  A high school basketball
player and the son of a head coach, he's been there and knows what it feels
like to be a part of the action.<Br>

<P>John Seitzinger - If you want to know anything about any sport here at
Marywood, John is the man for you.  The Sports Information Director and an
ex-head coach of the Lady Pacers, John not only has close contact with the all
the players, but with all the local players as well as officials.  He is the
stat man, everything from the leading scorer, down to a detail like steals per
game.  He brings a coach's mentality to the radio and helps dissect strategy.
Also a co-host and co-producer of <B>Pacer Pride</B>.<Br>

This file last updated on <B>April 23, 1996</B>


</DOC>
