<head>
<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  IHM Past:  Louis Florent Gillet:  Meeting 
Gillet</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>
<img src="../../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt=""><img 
src="../../Graphics/louis_gillet.gif" alt="Louis Florent Gillet"></h2><br>
<h2>More about Theresa Renauld's meeting Father Gillet</h2>
The following is taken from Sister Maria Alma's <cite>The Reverend Louis 
Florent Gillet:  His Life, Letters and Conferences</cite>. 
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
... we find [Father Gillet] giving the first French Mission in August, 
1843, at St. Paul's Church, Grosse Point, some ten miles from Detroit.  
Joseph Renauld, on whose land the church stood, gave hospitality to 
Father Gillet who, here for the first time, met Mr. Renauld's 
daughters.  The eldest, Theresa, acted as sacristan and at that time 
confided to the Redemptorist her desire to serve God more closely, 
adding that she had heard of religious but had never seen one.  Father 
Gillet taught Theresa the meaning of the Angelus and how to ring it 
three times daily, and promised her that very soon he would return, and 
try to arrange for the realization of her desire.
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
