<html>
<head>
<title>IHM Web:  About Us:  IHM Past:  Louis Florent Gillet:  Letter Nov 
4, 1892</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>
<img src="../../Graphics/ihmlogo3.gif" alt=""><img 
src="../../Graphics/louis_gillet.gif" alt="Louis Florent Gillet"></h2><br>
<h2>The Final Letter</h2>
<h3>November 4, 1892</h3>
<pre>
Abbaye
  de
N.D. d'Hautecombe			   Hautecombe, 4 November, 1892
  par Chindrieux
    Savoie
</pre>
<P>
My very dear sisters in Our Lord,
<P>
I gather the little strength which remains to me to address to you my 
last Adieux.  When you receive this letter, I shall be no more! ... I 
have received the Last Sacraments, and I await, in very great suffering, 
the visit of the Divine Lord.  Will you remember your father in Jesus 
Christ?  I count very much upon your prayers. ... After my death, the 
Reverend Father Prior will sent to Mother Superior a relic, and to 
Sister M. Clotilde my cross and rosary.
<P>
Adieu, my very dear and beloved Sisters!  I remain
<P>
<pre>
			Your affectionate Father in Our Lord,

						   F. Marie-Celestin
</pre>
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
[The relic of St. John Berchmans, the old Mission Cross which Father 
Gillet had used in Monroe, and which he had kept with him through the 
years, the rosary with its crucifix, are now in Villa Maria, West Chester, PA.]
<P>
<img src="../../Lines/sb10-1.gif" 
alt="____________________________________________________________________">
<P>
