<Head>
<TITLE> Marywood Communication Arts Program</TITLE>
<body background="/images/backgrnd.gif">
<Center>
<H1>The Marywood College <A href="comm.html">Communication Arts Home Page</A></H1>
<H2>TVM-37 & WVMW 91.5 FM</H2>
</center>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<HR>
<H3>Marywood College is...</H3>
...a liberal arts college located in Scranton, Pennsylvania, U.S.A. founded in
1915 by an order of the Sisters of the Immacualte Heart of Mary, I.H.M.
Originally opened as an all-girl school, Marywood went co-ed in the mid 70's.
<B>Telecommunications</B> is only one of the hundreds of graduate and
undergraduate degrees offered by the school. 
<H3><A HRef="http://ac.marywood.edu/www2/commarts/tvm.html">TVM-37</A></H3>
 and<H3><A HRef="http://ac.marywood.edu/www2/commarts/vmfm.html">WVWM 91.5FM</A></H3>
...are the student run television and radio stations that are based "in the
basement" of the Marywood College Learning Resources Center (Library) and are
operated by the Telecommunications Department. This site is let the public know
of the great work that is being produced by the college's students.
<HR>
<H3>For further information...</H3>
...on the college in general, we have set up three possible links from this
page.  You can go to:<Br>
<B><A HREF="http://ac.marywood.edu/aboutmw.htm">General Information about
Marywood</A></B><Br>
<B><A HRef="http://ac.marywood.edu/www2/guestbook/guestform.html">Sign the
Guestbook</A></B><Br>
<B><A HRef="http://ac.marywood.edu/schools.htm">Schools</A></B><Br>

<P>This file last updated on April 25, 1996<Br>
Copyright and copy, 1995.  All rights reserved 
</Body>
