<Center><Font Color=#FF0000><B><I>Obiter Dicta</I></B></Font>...Incidental statements made in passing. In a legal sense, statements in a court opinion that are not necessary to the decision, nor do they have binding precedential value. In the context <Br>of this page however, it means simply pages that are...</Center>

<Center><IMG src="hot2.gif" alt=""></Center>

<Center><IMG src="hline037.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Font Color=#FF0000><I><Font Size=+2><U>Search Engines</U></Font></I></Font>
<IMG align=bottom src="dogruns.gif" alt=""><P>

All of these search engines are superb<B>. . .</B>it really is a matter of personal preference. For best results, take the time to check out the query instructions, as some of them have their own particular idiosyncracies.<P>

<A href="http://www.altavista.digital.com" Alt="">AltaVista</A><Br>
<A href="http://www.excite.com" Alt="">Excite</A><Br>
<A href="http://www.hotbot.com/" Alt="">HotBot</A><Br>
<A href="http://www3.infoseek.com/" Alt="">Infoseek</A><Br>
<A href="http://www-msn.lycos.com/" Alt="">Lycos</A><Br>
<A href="http://www.search.com" Alt="">Magellan</A>
<P>
<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><B><I>"The welfare of the people is the highest law." </I></B><Br>Cicero, <I>De Legibus</I></Center>
<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Font Color=#FF0000><Font Size=+2><I><U>Law Related Directories & Search Engines</U></I></Font></Font><P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www.law.cornell.edu/index.html" Alt="">The Legal Information Institute</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> The pre-eminent source for U.S. court decisions and law related information on the Web.  Brought to you by Cornell law school, this site is indicative of why Cornell is in the top 10 U.S. law schools, and certainly #1 as far as being a Web resource.<P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> 
<A href="http://www.fedworld.gov/" Alt="">FedWorld Information Network</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt="">...If it has to do with a government organization, you can find the site through this directory. The place to start online when looking for government reports, studies and records.<P>


<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www.lectlaw.com" Alt="">The 'Lectric Law Library</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> Done with humour, style and imagination, the library's rooms are crammed with law related information. Even if you're not looking for anything in particular, its just fun to take the tour.<P> 

<IMG src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www.hg.org" Alt="">Hieros Gamos</A> <IMG src="redstar.gif" alt=""> HG bills itself as the largest legal site on the web, and it may well be true. Sponsored by 133 independent law firms, it has over 10,000 links. Worth a visit!<P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www.findlaw.com/index.html" Alt="">FindLaw</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> Another great legal directory and search engine. A special feature here is that you can register and subscribe to receive law review and law journal abstracts via e-mail...Free!<P>

<A href="http://www.law.indiana.edu/law/v-lib/lawindex.html" Alt="">World Wide Web Virtual Library - Law</A>...From the World Wide Web Consortium and Indiana University School of Law - Bloomington, a compilation of web resources indexed by organization type, topic, and search tools.<P>

<A href="http://www.yahoo.com/law/" Alt="">Yahoo!</A>...An old favorite.  Yahoo! directories cover just about everything, and their legal one is no exception.<P>

<A href="http://darkwing.uoregon.edu/~ddunn/l_schl.htm" Alt="">The Law Student Web</A>...From D. Kevin Dunn at the University of Oregon School of Law, a fine collection of web locations of interest to pre-law and law students.  Check out "Offbeat Court Opinions and Statutory Law".<P>

<A href="http://www.njlawnet.com/w3lawyer.html" Alt="">W3 Lawyer</A>...A searchable site from the New Jersey Law Network.  Covers a wide range of legal topics and resources.<P>

<A href="http://www.pbi.org/Links/palawlinks.html" Alt="">The Pennsylvania Bar Institute</A>...Links to Pennsylvania law-related web sites.<P>

<A href="http://lawlib.wuacc.edu/washlaw/washlaw.html" Alt="">WashLaw Web</A>...Yes, we are in Kansas.  From Washburn University School of Law, a comprehensive collection of law related resources on the web.<P>

<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><B><I>"A verbal contract isn't worth the paper its printed on."</I></B><Br>Attributed to Samuel Goldwyn, but sounds like Yogi Berra</Center>
<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Font Color=#FF0000><Font Size=+2><U><I>News On-Line</I></U></Font></Font><P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www1.pbs.org/newshour/" Alt="">Online Newshour</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt="">...Quality coverage of world events from the good people at PBS.  Includes transcripts of previous <I>Newshour With Jim Lehrer</I> programs and interviews along with RealAudio recordings.<P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www.ljx.com/indexhigh.html" Alt="">Law Journal Extra!</A> <IMG src="redstar.gif" alt=""> Legal Headlines, Decision of the Day, Internet related topics, links to case law, topics of interest to the practicing attorney, even legal trivia contests...all of these features and more combine to make this an excellent on-line publication.<P>

<A href="http://www.westpub.com/wlntop/front.htm" Alt="">West's Legal News</A>...From West Publishing, reporting of top court cases and legal news from around the country.  Updated daily Monday-Friday.<P>

<A href="http://www.nytimes.com" Alt="">The New York Times</A>...With a new slogan for their on-line version, all the news that's fit to download.<P>

<A href="http://washingtonpost.com/" Alt="">The Washington Post</A>...News from within the Beltway. Great international news section.<P>

<A href="http://www.sjmercury.com/" Alt="">The San Jose Mercury News</A>...From the Silicon Valley, perhaps the best example of an on-line newspaper.<P>

<A href="http://www.the-times.co.uk/" Alt="">The London Times</A>...Its always good to get another perspective. You have to register to view, but its free and well worth it. Cheers!<P>

<A href="http://www.scn.org/news/newspeak/" Alt="">American Newspeak</A>...Great satire on the top stories of the week.<P> 

<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><B><I>"The law, in its majestic equality, forbids the rich as well as the poor<Br>to sleep under bridges, to beg in the streets, and to steal bread."</I></B><Br>Anatole France</Center>
<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Font Color=#FF0000><Font Size=+2><U><I>Legal Miscellany</I></U></Font></Font><P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www.aclu.org/" Alt=""> American Civil Liberties Union</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> The place to go to find information on attempted restrictions of essential rights re free speech, racial equality, women's rights, student's rights, cyber-liberties, et al.<P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> <A href="http://www.bart.nl/~geradts/forensic.html" Alt="">Zeno's Forensic Page</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> Links to everything you ever wanted to know about forensic science, forensic medicine and forensic psychiatry. A very comprehensive collection.<P>

<A href="http://www.pbus.com" Alt="">Professional Bail Agents of the U.S.</A>...Among other items of interest, "bail skips" and Most Wanted.<P>

<A href="http://lcweb.loc.gov/homepage/lchp.html" Alt="">The Library of Congress</A>...Visit <B><U>the</U></B> library. Exhibitions, an awesome catalog, copyright information, a research and reference department, global legal information and more.<P>

<A href="http://lawyers.martindale.com/marhub" Alt="">Martindale Lawyer Locator</A>...From the Martindale-Hubbell Law Directory, find lawyers, law firms, or other legal personnel.  Locate by name, firm, area of practice, location or language.<P>

<A href="http://www.columbia.edu/acis/bartleby/" Alt="">Bartleby Library</A>...From Columbia University, named after Melville's renowned scrivener ("I would prefer not to."), this is a very fine collection of 19th and early 20th century prose and poetry <B>on-line</B>.  They have to wait for works to go out of copyright, and they are continually adding to the collection.<P>

<A href="http://www.courttv.com/" Alt="">Court TV Law Center</A>...For those who just can't get enough of the "sensational" on TV, here you go. Aside from that, an interesting games section whereby you are presented with a fact pattern and arguments and you decide the case.<P>

<Font Color=#FF0000><Font Size=+2><U><I>Phone, Mail & Geographic Directories</I></U></Font></Font><P>

<A href="http://www.four11.com" Alt="">Four11</A>...Search for E-Mail, telephone, NetPhone and Government listings.<P>

<A href="http://www.switchboard.com/" Alt="">Switchboard</A>...A nifty white pages directory where you can not only search for other folks listed in published phone directories, but also allows you to personalize your own listing.<P>

<A href="http://www.mapquest.com" Alt="">Mapquest</A>...If you have an address, this interactive atlas allows you to locate it on the map.<P>

<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><B><I>"You can observe a lot by just watching"</I></B><Br>Yogi Berra</Center>
<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<Font Color=#FF0000><Font Size=+2><U><I>Web Page Resources</I></U></Font></Font><P>

<IMG align=bottom src="hot1.gif" alt=""><IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt="">
<A href="http://www.arachnoid.com/index.html" Alt="">WebThing</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""><IMG align=bottom src="hot1.gif" alt="">Want to create your own web page? This is the place to download one of the finest web editors on this planet.  Paul Lutus has provided not only some great software, but a challenging philosophy as well. Take the time to read about "<B>CareWare</B>". <B>Free!</B> Thanks Paul. <P>

<IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> 
<A href="http://subnet.virtual-pc.com/~le387818/" Alt="">The HTML Reference Library</A> <IMG align=bottom src="redstar.gif" alt=""> An excellent supplement and reference work to download for anyone, especially the newcomer, who is building their own web page.  Lots of great features. <B>Free!</B> Thanks to Stephen LeHunte!<P>

<A href="http://informant.dartmouth.edu/" Alt="">The Informant</A>...From Dartmouth comes this handy service that "will save your favorite keyword queries and URL's, check them periodically, and send you email whenever there are new or updated web pages". <B>Free!</B><P>

<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center>
<Center><B><I>"The life of the law has not been logic; it has been experience."</I></B><Br>Mr. Justice Holmes, <I>The Common Law</I></Center>
<Center><IMG src="colbartn.gif" alt=""></Center><P>

<IMG align=center src="eye_bar.gif" alt=""><BR>

