<br>
<center><font size=6 color="#00ff00"><em>Who are we?</em><br></font></center>
<font size=4>
We are a small NON-profit-making organisation originally based in the UK but now made up of amateur scopers, 
naturalists, microscopists, artists, writers, teachers, and software writers from different countries.
We share a common passion: we are all interested in the world around us!
More than this... we like to explore our world by understanding its construction
and maintenance from those things which remain almost secretively invisible because
they work on a tiny scale - a microscopic world! We are dedicated to promoting a fun and interesting way
to others of finding out a whole lot more about our amazing universe we live in.
<br>
<br>
It is difficult to define roles. We are a loosly knit bunch of people and we all help out on all aspects of 
running the various sites and co-ordinating non-web activities. You can contact any of us from the list below but
if you want a first point of contact, try your local Site or Site-Mirror Editor first, or pump your mail into the CENTRAL ADDRESS at the bottom of the page.
We are all amateurs. Don't let the fancy list of names and descriptions scare you off! We are just ordinary folk 
having a go at something worthwhile. Please write in and chat with us!
<br>
<br>
</font>
<P>
<center><font size=6><a href="thecrew.html">See our Mug-Shots?</A></font></center>
