<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>www.microscopy-uk.org.uk - 3D Microscopy : holograms, anaglyphs</TITLE></HEAD><BODY bgcolor="#000000" text="#00ff00"><a name="top"><center><h4>www.microscopy-uk.org.uk : "Pioneering Microscopy on the Web!"</h4><h4>"You are not alone!"<br>2907 cross-eyed users have been here since  April 7th 1996</h4><br><img src="title.gif"></center><p><center><IMG SRC="3dmic1.jpg"  ALT=""></center><P><center><h1>3D MICROSCOPY ON Microscopy UK</h1> <strong>Note: You need Netscape 1.11 or later version to browse here!</strong></center><p><h4><center><table><tr><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <a href="#about">About this section</A></td> <td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <a href="#howto">How to take 3D Microscopy pics.</A></td></tr><tr><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <a href="#select">Select a 3D image to view</A></td><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <a href="http://www.molcol.demon.co.uk/index.htm">3D Planet-Scopers</A></td></td></tr></table></center></h4><p><br><a name="about"><center><h2>Seeing in 3D</h2></center>To view this section you will need 3D glasses. These may come in variousforms but the ones to use here must have a red lens and a blue lens; the redlens being for your left eye. We will shortly list where you can obtain glasses from cheaply.<p><center><h2>Browser</h2></center>You will need Netscape Version 1.11, 1.22, or 2.0 as your browser or a <em>helper</em> applicationto see the images which are in GIF or JPG format. Most large images are *.jpg (JPEG)files in 24bit colour.<p><center><h2>Stereo and Holograms</h3></center>Images in this area are either true stereo 3D, or holograms.All of them require viewing through red/blue 3D glasses.<p><a name="howto"><center><h2>How to get 3-D Microscopy Pics</h2></center>Watch this space! We will shortly be offering a serious of articles designedto help the amateur microscopist capture their very own 3-D Microscopy pics.<p><br><br><A name="select"><center><h3><i>Select from below</i></h3></center><br><center><table><tr><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="bio.html">Biology Pics</A></td><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="insects.html">Insect Pics</A></td><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="scopes.html">Microscope Pics</A></td><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="botany.html">Botany Pics</A></td></tr><tr><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="inorgan.html">Inorganic Pics</A></td><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="fossils.html">Micro-fossil Pics</A></td><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="misc.html">Misc. Pics</A></td><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="star.html">Super Pics</A></td></td></tr><tr><td><img src="glasses.gif" align=top> <A href="sem.html">SEM IMAGES</A></td></tr></table></center><br><br><br><h3><br><h3><center><a href="#Top">Top of page</A><br><a href="../../index.html">Go to Microscopy-uk Front Page</A></center></h3><br><h4><center>Comments and errors to <a href="mailto:mol@molcol.demon.co.uk">The Editor</A></center></h4><br><br><h6>(c) www.microscopy-uk.org.uk and Micscape Magazine 1995-96 UK. All images are copyright of Microscopy UK or their contributors. Images may be downloaded for personal use only, or for use on small projects in schools or clubs. Reproduction for commercial use is prohibited without permission fromthe image author. Write to either the  Micscape Editor or the Microscopy UK Editor if you need further details on rightsof use. Reviewers of Web sites may reproduce a single page in their reviews without obtainingfurther permission. Other web sites are welcome to link to our site without writing for permission.</h6></BODY></HTML>
