<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>www.microscopy-uk.org.uk - Microscopy & Biology for Schools  </TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY  BGCOLOR="#C9F1C5"  vlink="#007fff" link="#ff0000" alink="#aa0000">

<CENTER>
<a name="top">
<H1>SCHOOL RESOURCES from www.microscopy-uk.org.uk</H1><strong>Text by: Alan Maude, Images by M.Smith.</strong>
<P>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
Welcome to microscopy-uk's section to help provide free 
resources to schools,students, and colleges. If you are 
involved with learning or teaching Biology,you will find 
many of our pages interesting but this section is perhaps 
the most useful to you.
<p>
<center>
<h3><a href="#links">School-Link</A> | <a href="#mammal">Mammal Biology</A> | <a href="#plant">Plant Biology</A></h3>
</center>
<p>
<center><H3><A HREF="../index.html">microscopy-uk front screen</A></H3></center>
<P>
<p>
<h3><em>Now available from these pages:-</em></h3>
<ul>
<a href="http://www.micropix.demon.co.uk/schools/lectures/lectures.htm">The Brunel Lectures</A>: complete audio and visual streams (still images) on topical 
biology subjects. First one will be on the Human Lung. You will
need the RealAudio Sound Player to hear the Audio streams
(See our Front page to obtain <a href="../index.html#helpers">helper applications</A>).
</ul>

<h3><em>Why not get involved with the Worldwide Amateur Project:-</em></h3>

<ul>
We have launched a worldwide project which should appeal to a wide range 
of young people. Here is a chance to get your students involved in something 
interesting whichwill also prove to be a lot of fun and yet provide a 
real life example of organised research. 
Check out <a href="../project/jointven.html">The Project</A>
</ul>
<HR>

