<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>www.microscopy-uk.org.uk - Amateur Microscopy Clubs & People </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="peop.gif" TEXT="#000066" VLINK="#7F3F7F" LINK="#CF3FCF">

<center><h1>Amateur Microscopy: Clubs & People</h1></center>

<font size=4>
Nothing ever happens without people! This section is dedicated to the 
human endeavour of providing something of worth, not for financial gain, but simply
because they are driven down a path of love or passion to offer something they consider 
valuable to others. Often such a road can be long and winding, and may only be travelled
by many helping each other. Sometimes a single pioneer can make the journey alone filled
with the belief that others will follow. 
<p>
Take a moment here to see where other people are spending time to follow their passion, or 
have made a positive difference to all of our lives!
<p>
</font>
<center><h3> Groups of people </h3>

<b>
<a href="http://www.hull.ac.uk/Hull/AB_Web/HMS_95_96_prog.html">HULL MICROBIOLOGICAL SOCIETY</A><BR>
<A href="./qmc/rms.html">RMS (READING MICROSCOPICAL SOCIETY)</a><br>
<A href="./qmc/mainqmc.html">THE QUEKETT MICROSCOPICAL CLUB</a><br>
<A href="./qmc/nsclub.html">NORTHAMPTONSHIRE NATURAL HISTORY SOCIETY</A><br>
<A href="./qmc/pmca.html">POSTAL MICROSCOPICAL CLUB OF AUSTRALIA</A><br>
</b>

<h3>Hall of Fame</h3>
<b>
<a href="./qmc/hero1.html">JOHN BENJAMIN DANCER</A><br>

</b>
</center>
<center>
<H3>
<center><h1><strong><a href="../index.html">Go to Microscopy-uk Front Page</A></strong></h1></center>

</H3>
</center>

<HR>
<P>
<h5>
Microscopy UK are offering space in this section for the any amateur 
microscopical society to advertise their activities.
<P>
This service is provided for two reasons. First and foremost, if you live 
near the societies' base, why not join the society and support their activities!
<P>
Secondly, we hope it is of interest to our international readers to see the
scope of the activities provided for the amateur microscopist. We hope 
that Microscopy UK may provide a forum for the friendly exchange of ideas, tips 
and articles between amateur microscopists Worldwide.
<A HREF="mailto:mol@molcol.demon.co.uk">Please contact us</A> if you 
are involved with an amateur microscopy society anywhere in the world, and 
you have some ideas or contributions to share.
</h5>
<P>
<CENTER>
<br>
<br>
<H5> Please report any errors to: <a href="mailto:mol@molcol.demon.co.uk">The Editor</A></H5>
</CENTER>

