<HEAD>
<TITLE>UK/US JOINT VENTURE MICROSCOPY PROJECT</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" BACKGROUND="http://www.molcol.demon.co.uk/marly/mic1-bg.gif" WIDTH=135 HEIGHT=196>

<A NAME="TOP"></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=-2>
<CENTER>
Copyright  1996 Microscopy-UK
</CENTER>
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="jtvnpj.gif" WIDTH=284 HEIGHT=275></IMG>
</CENTER>
</P>
<P>
<CENTER>
<H1>UK/US Joint Venture Microscopy Project</H1>
</CENTER>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<JUSTIFY>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="t.gif" WIDTH=34 HEIGHT=44><FONT SIZE=+2>he <I>UK/US Joint Venture Microscopy Project</I> is an effort of Microscopy-UK, a <I>not-for-profit</I> organization. Its purpose is to spark new interest in the hobby of microscopy and to promote the exchange of cultural and scientific ideas among peoples of different Nations by using the Internet as the medium for this exchange. Through this effort, we hope to change the way people perceive the world around them and to promote peace and harmony among Nations by proving that we, as people, can work together, peacefully, toward a common goal.
</IMG></FONT></JUSTIFY></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>
If your school, science club or microscopy club would like to participate in this <I>history making event</I>, please contact the Project Coordinator in your Country by clicking on the representative flag of your Nation, 
<A HREF="#COORDINATORS">below</A>. 
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>
Schools or organizations from other Nations wishing to participate in a Joint Venture Microscopy Project should contact the 
<A HREF="MAILTO: rmcain@pipeline.com">International Project Data Coordinator</A> (English only, please.). 
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=-1>
<CENTER>
| <A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A>
| <A HREF="#REQUIREMENTS">Requirements</A>
| <A HREF="#FUNDING">Funding</A>
| <A HREF="#DESCRIPTION">Description</A>
| <A HREF="#COORDINATORS">Coordinators</A> |<BR>
| <A HREF="../index.html">Microscopy-UK</A> 
| <A HREF="http://www.molcol.demon.co.uk/">
| <A HREF="http://www.molcol.demon.uk/marly/marlyadv.htm">Marly's Micronauts</A>|
</CENTER>
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<HR SIZE=3>

<A NAME="REQUIREMENTS"></A>
<P>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR="#FF0000">
<H1>Participation Requirements</H1>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
Schools or clubs desiring to participate should select five (5) students, or members, between ages 15-18, and one adult over 21 to act as Group Supervisor. The Group should have access to a low powered microscope (100x-300x at least) and a connection to the Internet with a minimum of an email (electronic mail)  account. Ideally, the Internet connection should include individual email accounts for each participant, World Wide Web and Internet Relay Chat access - 
although it is only necessary to have email access to participate!
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
Each participant must submit a recent photograph of themselves along with a written introduction, giving their name, interests and personal achievements to their National Project Co-ordinator.
If possible, the introduction should be a 60 second video-taped, self-introduction - although this is not a necessity.
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
At a minimum, each Group must file a <I>Project Progress Report</I> with the 
<A HREF="MAILTO: rmcain@pipeline.com">International Project Data Coordinator</A>, or your National Coordinator, by email, every fifteen (15) days. Failure of a Group to timely file a <I>Project Progress Report</I> may cause that Group to be dismissed from the Project. Reasonable extensions of time may be granted by your National Coordinator.
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=-1>
<CENTER>
| <A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A> 
| <A HREF="#FUNDING">Funding</A> 
| <A HREF="#DESCRIPTION">Description</A> 
| <A HREF="#COORDINATORS">Coordinators</A> |<BR>
| <A HREF="../index.html">Microscopy-UK</A> 
| <A HREF="http://www.molcol.demon.co.uk/">Planet Scopers</A> 
| <A HREF="http://www.molcol.demon.co.uk/marly/marlyadv.htm">
Marly's Micronauts</A> |
</CENTER>
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<HR SIZE=3>

<A NAME="FUNDING"></A>
<P>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR="#FF0000">
<H1>Project Funding</H1>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
Each Group must provide its own operational funding. Groups <I>OFFICIALLY</I> recognized by Microscopy-UK as active, participating members of the <I>Joint Venture Microscopy Project</I> are permitted to freely, but tastefully use the <I>Joint Venture Microscopy Project</I> 
<A HREF="#LOGO">Logo</A> for fund raising activities and to solicit Community support. It is envisaged that the project costs for participants will be nominal only.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=+1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">
(PLEASE NOTE: The Copyright Notice must NOT be removed from the <I>Joint Venture Microscopy Project</I> Logo under any circumstances. Removal of the Copyright Notice from the <I>Joint Venture Microscopy Project</I> Logo constitutes a violation of International Law and will be prosecuted to the fullest extent possible.)
</FONT>
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<A NAME="LOGO"></A>
<P>
<STRONG>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
<H2>Download <I>Joint Venture Microscopy Project</I> Logo</H2>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=-1>
| <A HREF="ftp://members.aol.com/marlycain/jvlogo_c.gif">Full Color (8K)</A> 
| <A HREF="ftp://members.aol.com/marlycain/jvlogo_g.gif">Gray Scale (8K)</A> | 
</FONT>
</CENTER>
</STRONG>
</P>
<BR>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=-1>
<CENTER>
| <A HREF="#TOP">Top of Page</A> 
| <A HREF="#REQUIREMENTS">Requirements</A> 
| <A HREF="#DESCRIPTION">Description</A> 
| <A HREF="#COORDINATORS">Coordinators</A> |<BR>
| <A HREF="../index.html">Microscopy-UK</A> 
| <A HREF="http://www.molcol.demon.co.uk/">
Planet Scopers</A> 
| <A HREF="http://www.molcol.demon.co.uk/marly/marlyadv.htm">
Marly's Micronauts</A> |
</CENTER>
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<HR SIZE=3>

<A NAME="DESCRIPTION"></A>
<P>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR="#FF0000">
<H1>Project Description</H1>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
<I>The focal point of the Project:</I> to record images, observations, and other information about dustmites, their habitat, population quantities, life-cycle and any other findings regarding their existence. Dustmites were selected as the focal point of this Project because they should be readily available in most peoples' homes, in their beds, their vacuum cleaners, their carpets, etc..
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
<I>The objective of the Project:</I> to use amateur microscopy skills and interactively <I>invent</I> the tools needed to record images of and information about dustmites; use participant ingenuity and interaction to find a simplistic, extremely inexpensive solution using common, ordinary household items, such as posterboard, tape, paperclips, rubberbands, etc.; generate a rich exchange of ideas between participants and groups to find the most simplistic, inexpensive method(s) to conduct the focal point activity: recording images of and information about dustmites.
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
Only inexpensive, common, household items may be utilized, so everyone has an equal opportunity to participate. Beyond the use of a microscope and a household camera, no eleborate commercial tools may be used. The Project is to be an exercise in ingenuity; an interactive collaboration between groups from different Nations to utilize amateur microscopy skills to conduct the focal point activity: recording images of and information about dustmites.
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
As participants record images and information, they should submit their information and images to the 
<A HREF="MAILTO: rmcain@pipeline.com">International Project Data Coordinator</A>, where it will be formatted and posted on the World Wide Web. If a participating group is unable to 
convert their images, for example - photos or drawings, into electronic format, then your National Project Co-Ordinator will assist you. Contact the National coordinator for details and arrangement.
</P>
<P>
Participants will maintain their copyright to any information they gather, but provide Microscopy-UK and the Internet Youth Group limited publishing rights. At Project completion, if the data and images gathered by the participants are determined to be significant, a collective scientific paper will be entered on the participants' behalf, submitting their results, recognizing the work of each individual participant, their contribution to the collective effort and their contribution to the Scientific Community in the study of dustmites. Such an achievement would make the participants very attractive to Universities, Scholarship Organizations, etc.. 
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
In order for results to be considered significant, documentation is of paramount importance. Participants must, of course, record their findings, but they must also record the methods used for discovery and the reasoning behind the methods used for that discovery. As much of the thought processes invloved, as possible, as well as the resultant findings must be recorded, to validate the discovery, for submission as a bonafide scientific document.
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
The Project has been designed to provide an excellent opportunity for participants, not only to exercise their <I>thinking muscles</I>, but to share pieces of their culture, make friends in faraway places and to better themselves and improve their world. This is NOT to be a competition between two National Groups, but an open exchange of ideas and information between participants, to find a solution to reach a common goal. 
</FONT></STRONG>
</P>
<P>
<STRONG>
