<hr SIZE=12>
<h2> ABOUT MICROSCOPY UK</H2>
The original ABOUT page has been removed. Microscopy UK is constantly 
changing and updating. The best way to learn about what is going on is
by exploring. Keep an eye out for notes and tips especially on the 
very <a href="index.html">front screen</A> which will help keep you posted 
on changes taking place. You can read a little more about us at the bottom of the front 
screen!
<p>
Our site is a vibrant one with new things being added all of the time!
It is also YOUR site. Tell us what you like and don't like. We are not getting 
paid for the all the work we put in; it is for love alone! Don't be 
shy of chatting to us: it makes everything all worthwhile just to hear from you.
Click on any <em>Editor</em> tag and drop us a note!
<p>
Use your Browser's 'BACK' option to return to the last page you were viewing or 
maybe you would like to go to<a href="index.html#selection">The Front Page Selection Area.</A><br>
</center>
