<TITLE>MICSCAPE(microscopy) - The Quekett Microscopical Club </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#CDF9FF" TEXT="#0000B3" LINK="#C70000" VLINK="#009900" ALINK="#C50000">
<CENTER><H3>MICROSCOPY UK / MICSCAPE - Microscopy Society Information</h3></CENTER>
<hr>

<center>
<IMG SRC="qmclogo.gif" ALT=""  ALIGN=center>
<H2> THE QUEKETT MICROSCOPICAL CLUB</h2><BR>
<h3>Founded 1865<BR><BR>
<i>incorporating</i><BR>
THE PHOTOMICROGRAPHIC SOCIETY<BR></h3>
</center>
<hr>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=4><h3>The Club</h3>
The "Quekett" is a Scientific Society which exists for the friendly exchange of ideas
between people interested in light microscopy. It was begun well over a century ago for those
using the microscope as a recreation, but many professionals have always been members.  Some 
members are experts in their fields but are glad to share their knowledge with other members, whether
they be experts themselves, novices, or amateur microscopists. It is this friendly exchange which has
come to be the strength of the Quekett.
<p>

<ul>
<li> <A HREF="aboutqmc.html"> Welcome to the QMC</A> - (A quick tour of the Quekett)<br>
<li> <A HREF="aboutqmc.html#join"> Come and join us</A> - (How to become a member from anywhere in the world)<br>
<li> <A HREF="aboutqmc.html#publications"> Quekett Publications </A> - (Journals and Bulletins)<br>
<li> <A HREF="joinqmc.html"> The Committee </A> - (Contact details of the QMC committee)<br>
</ul>


