<HEAD><TITLE>MICROSCOPY UK / MICSCAPE Microscopy Clubs -  Postal Microscopical Club of Australia PMCA</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#CAF3FF" TEXT="#000096" LINK="#C70000" VLINK="#00B9B3" ALINK="#C70000">

<HR>
<center><H2>POSTAL MICROSCOPICAL CLUB OF AUSTRALIA (P.M.C.A)</H2></center>
<HR><FONT SIZE=4>
<BODY><BR>


The information below briefly describes the Club and its activities.<P>

More details including how to join the Club can be found on the <A HREF="http://www.pnc.com.au/~dingley"><STRONG>PMCA Web page</STRONG></A>.<P>


The Club promotes microscopes and microscopy in a practical way. Members can elect to become
OFF CIRCUIT MEMBERS and receive our Newsletter "Amateur Microscopist" three times a
year. <P>ON CIRCUIT MEMBERS receive the Newsletter and are also placed on a circuit to receive
sets of prepared microscope slides to examine in their own time. Members who live in or near
Sydney participate in Sunday excursions to collect and examine specimens and meet with people
with similar interests. Members in other states are encouraged to promote their own excursions.<P>

                   
                                


