<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>MICROSCOPY UK / MICSCAPE - Microscopy Society Information, Quekett Microscopical Club</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#CDF9FF" TEXT="#0000B3" LINK="#C70000" VLINK="#009900" ALINK="#C50000">
<CENTER><H3>MICROSCOPY UK / MICSCAPE - Microscopy Society Information</h3></CENTER>
<hr>
<center>
<IMG SRC="qmclogo.gif" ALT=""  ALIGN=center>
<H2> THE QUEKETT MICROSCOPICAL CLUB</h2><BR>
<h3>Founded 1865<BR><BR>
<i>incorporating</i><BR>
THE PHOTOMICROGRAPHIC SOCIETY<BR></h3>
</center>
<hr>
<center>
 <BR>

<h2>What the club has to offer</h2>
</center>
<center>
<h3>Meetings at the Natural History Museum</h3></center>
<img src="quek4.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=8 align=left>
<FONT SIZE=4>The club arranges a full programme of meetings. Besides formal lectures,

a <b>Gossip Meeting </b> is held most months , with informal demonstrations of apparatus
and specimens and an exchange of ideas in a relaxed atmosphere. A special interest of many members is photomicrography
and more recently - the use of video cameras and microcomputers in microscopy. Help and advice on getting started is 
assured from other members who have done their path-finding.
<p>
<img src="quek3.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=right>
The Quekett has been established for over 150 years and is always willing to try new ideas and techniques, making it
one of the most forward-looking clubs whilst maintaining
the best traditions and skills of the past. The gossip meetings provide the backbone of the club, providing a regular forum for skills 
and enthusiasm to percolate between members of different age groups and backgrounds.
</center>

<p>
<h3>The Library </h3>
Our library covers most aspects of Microscopy and allied topics. Most books can be borrowed by UK members, in person
or by post. Sets of slides are similarly available for borrowing, and in addition the Club has a fine reference of slides
which can be seen by arrangement.
<p>

<h3>Young Members</h3>
<img src="quek5.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=right>
There is a special class of membership for young people who vary in age from 5th
form to advanced student of under 21 where the subscription rate is almost halved
though the benefits remain in full. Young members are very welcome and can be
put in touch with other young members. Senior members of the club are often 
accomplished experts in their own fields and can therefore provide much help 
and encouragement to the younger ones. 
<p>
<h3>The Annual Exhibition</h3>
<img src="quek6.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=0 align=left>
Our major event is the <b>Annual Exhibition of Microscopy</b> each October, where members and others show
their work and inspire visitors to try things for themselves. On other occasions <b>tutorial sessions</b> are 
held for beginners, who learn rapidly under under the personal guidance of experienced members. All these meetings
are held in the Natural History Museum in South Kensington, which is an ideal setting for our interests, enjoying
the active support of the museum authorities.
<p>
<h3>The Annual Conference</h3>
A two-day conference is held each year by rotation in different parts of the country to bring together members from
those parts to hear a wide variety of speakers and to observe laboratory demonstrations of microscopical equipment 
and methods. (In 1997 it is being held in Bristol).
<p>
<h3>Field Excursions</h3>
<img src="quek2.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=right>
Field excursions are held several times a year. The members meet at good collecting sites under the guidance of 
expert naturalists. Much material for later preparation is obtained with plenty of advice on to deal with it.
These events are ideal for helping new-comers to learn more about microscopy as a dynamic hobby where detective
work, investigation, and study is linked to the real world and different environments. They can be great fun, and
provide an ideal place for members to relax and share their interests. 
<p>
<A name="publications">
<center>
<h3>Publications</h3>

<img src="queklog2.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=4 ></center><br>
Another strength is our publications. A Bulletin (in bound form) is currently issued twice a year, giving informal
records of meetings, news of events and the future programme. All members are encouraged
to contribute to this publication, for it is a helpful source of hints and tips and inspiration.
<p>

The Club's formal journal is called the <B>Quekett Journal of Microscopy</B> and this also is issued twice a year. Its circulation is 
world-wide and enables our overseas members to remain firmly linked to other members of the club despite being 
unable to attend the regular events in the UK. It is an exceptional source of papers on all aspects of light
microscopy, present and past, and with much emphasis upon the practical. The journal is well illustrated in line
and half tone, and past issues become a unique reference of very readable articles.
<p>
The journals are respected for their unique content and therefore are in demand even by non-members. Copies may be 
purchased by non-members. It is published on 1 April and 1 October each year and is available to <b>non-members</b>
for 30.00 pounds per annum in UK and Europe, 40.00 pounds (or 60.00 US Dollars) per annum elsewhere in the world.
Orders may be placed with any bookseller or with the <A href="joinqmc.html#contact">subscription manager</A>.
<p>
<I>The Quekett Journal of Microscopy</i> in addition to distribution to members, is acquired, either by purchase or
journal exchange, by over 60 scientific societies and libraries.

<A NAME="join">
<p>
<center><h3>Membership Details and How to Join the Quekett</h3></center>
You do not need to be an expert to join us. We welcome newcomers to amateur microscopy. What we do know is that once 
you join us, you will enjoy the benefits of belonging to one of the most historical and friendliest clubs for amateur
microscopists. The yearly subscription entitles members to all privileges of the Club, including free copies of <i>The 
Quekett Journal of Microscopy</i> and the <i>Bulletin.</i> Membership rates are UK26.00 pounds per annum in the UK and 
mainland Europe, elsewhere in the world is UK32.00 pounds (or US55.00 Dollars). Young members may join in, in UK only,
for UK10.00 pounds per annum. <b><A HREF="joinqmc.html"> Would you like to join us?</A></b>
<P>
<br>


<center> <A HREF="../../index.html">Microscopy UK Front Screen</A> <br>
<br>
                                    (OR)<br>
<br>
            <A HREF="mainqmc.html">Return to Quekett Front Page</A> <br>
            <A HREF="../mainpeop.html">People & Clubs Front Page</A> <br>
       
</center>
<p>
<P>
<P><HR>
<center><H5> Please report any errors to: <a href="mailto:dave@diwalk.demon.co.uk">Dave Walker</A></H5></center>

Microscopy UK are offering FREE space in this section for any amateur 
microscopical society to advertise their activities.
<P>
We hope 
that Microscopy UK / Micscape may provide a new medium for the friendly exchange of ideas, tips and articles between amateur microscopists worldwide.<P>
<A HREF="mailto:mol@molcol.demon.co.uk">Please contact us</A> if you 
are involved with an amateur microscopy society anywhere in the world, and 
you have some ideas or contributions to share.<P>

</FONT>
