<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>www.microscopy-uk.org.uk : SEM Microscopy - Orion </TITLE></HEAD>

<a name="top">
<BODY bgcolor="#000000" text="#ffbbff" vlink="#7f00ff" link="#ff7f00" background="../stars.gif">

<img src="orion.jpg" align=left vspace=12> 
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<h1><em>welcomes you to...</em></h1>
<br clear>
<img src="../xline.gif"><br clear>
<center><h2><em>...enhanced image-capture for Windows.</em></h2></center>
<img src="../xline.gif"><br clear>
<br>
<font size=4>
Our offer is to provide you with a complete solution for grabbing, processing, storing and printing high resolution, ultra high quality
images from your SEM, TEM or optical microscope. It is a <em><strong>complete solution</strong></em> with
a stand-alone grabbing system designed for efficiency and unsurpassed image quality.
</font>
<p>
<a name="about">
<center>
<h2><em>Scroll down or select from below to find out about:-</em></h2>
<img src="../xline2.gif"><br clear>
<p>
<strong>
<a href="#images">Image Characteristics</A><br>
<a href="#macro">Macro commands execution</A><br>
<a href="#system">System options</A><br>
<a href="#addition">Additional features - automatic system</A><br>
<a href="#word1">Macro commands and extensions for Word 6</A><br>
<a href="#word2">Macro commands and extensions for Word 6 the Philips XL SEMs</A><br>
<a href="orion2.html">Sample images</A><br>
<a href="mailto:orion@infoboard.be">Contact us now for more INFORMATION</a> <br>
</strong>
<p>
<img src="../xline2.gif"><br clear>
</center>
<p>
<h3>To contact us:-</h3>
<strong>
Please leave your messages or questions at one of the following addresses / locations:<br>

<ul>
<img src="../bullet.gif" align=top> Email: orion@infoboard.be (main offices in Belgium)<br>
<img src="../bullet.gif" align=top> I.C.I. sarl in France - Tel: (33) 84 58 02 43, Fax: (33) 84 54 03 98<br>
</ul>

</strong>
<p>
<br><br>

<a name="images">
<h2>Characteristics of the digitized images</h2>

<h4>
<pre>
<ul>
<li>A grabbed image is immediately available in the 
PC ram for printing processing, storage or transfer
to any other application.

<li>The images are stored in 256 gray levels per pixel
(integration modes use 16 bits per pixel during grabbing)

<li>Images can be processed, filtered, mixed, extracted
manually or automatically

<li>User can write lines, rectangles or texts of any size
in the image

<li>A line function is also available for gray level analysis
</ul>
</pre>
</h4>
<p>
<center><strong><a href="#about">Return to about...</A></strong></center>
<p>



<a name="macro">
<h2>Introduction and characteristics</h2>
<strong>Orion 4 is designed to work in the Windows 3 environment. A 32-bits version for Windows NT is being designed and will be available soon. 
Orion grabs images in any size between 16 x 16 to 4096 x 4096 pixels, 256 gray levels, from the SEM slow scan and photo modes. Practically, the exact image size is a function of the scanning characteristics.
<p>
Orion connects to ALL existing SEMs. Every SEM has a corresponding driver on disk which holds all the information to configure the board and establish a working range of desired image sizes (max. 64 images sizes can be defined per driver).
<p>
The connection is simple (4 wires) and the board provides <em>total electrical isolation</em> between the PC and the SEM electronics. This provides optimal security and unequaled image quality because of the suppression of the induced noise. It also protects your SEM against unwanted noise induction in the SEM video circuitry. The SEM electronics do <em>not</em> need to be modified in any way. The image quality you will get can be compared with the quality you would get with active systems, but without any risk.
<p>
You also get square pixels in any mode; this is useful for image analysis and avoiding distortion when the images are passed to other packages for display, processing, etc ...
<p>
Depending on the connection, it is possible to simultaneously grab two images (the Orion board has two video inputs), so you could grab an image from the SE detector, and another one from the BSE at the same time, in only one scan.
</strong>
<p>
<p>
<center><strong><a href="#about">Return to about...</A></strong></center>
<p>
<p>
<a name="system">
<h2>Orion system options</h2>
<strong>
<dl>
<dt><h3><img src="../bullet.gif" align=top> Macro command interpretor</h3>
<p>
<dd>This extremely powerful function enables you to redefine nearly everything in the Orion package - buttons, main menu type, grabbing process.
    It can help you save time by executing different grabbing routines and functions depending on the current user.
    It can also be used to launch external tasks like a word processor or an image analysis system for immediate image processing.
    New commands are added to the interpretor nearly every week.
<p>
<dt><h3><img src="../bullet.gif" align=top> EDX mapping channels</h3>
<p>
<dd>This facility for 'grabbing' allows superimposed elemental maps with grabbed image
    This option allows simultaneous grabbing of an SE or BSE image, and up to 8 EDX mappings channels. This option requires the use of         a VEGA board. All images are displayed simultaneously on the PC screen.
<p>
<dt><h3><img src="../bullet.gif" align=top> Photo resolution replay board</h3>
<p>
<dd>This allows image to be sent back to the SEM photo device
    This very high resolution board connects to the Orion board and has a max. resolution of 4096 x 4096 pixels, 256 gray levels. Any         image up to that size can be sent to the photo device; usually the result quality is at least equal to the quality of the original         photograph.
<p>
<dt><h3><img src="../bullet.gif" align=top> HP Laserjet enhancement card</h3>
<p>
<dd>This produces photographic quality images on paper in 10 seconds print time.
    When it is required to print nearly photographic quality images at low cost, we propose to use the LazardPrint board. This board         prints in 150, 300 and even 600 true dpi, in 256 gray levels from a palette of 1024. The results are fast and impressive (10         seconds are usually required to print a 1100 x 1600 pixels image with a Pentium PC).
</dl>
</strong>

<p>
<center><strong><a href="#about">Return to about...</A></strong></center>
<p>

<a name="addition">

<h2>Additional features - making the Orion system automatic</h2>
<strong>
<dl>
<dt><h3><img src="../bullet.gif" align=top>1. Macro examples </h3>
<dd>
</dl>
<p>
<strong>
<em>Want to automatically grab a photo, make an interpolated reduction of 2, include your logo at the bottom and put it in a predefined         document in Word 6 (or any other word processor) ?????</em>
<p>
Create the following macro:-<br>
</strong>
<p>
<table cellpadding=8>
<tr>
<td><strong>GrabPhoto 2, 5, 1,</strong></td><td><strong><em>(grab an image in photo mode use format no 5, use input no 1, and put image in Gallery position 2)</em><strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>ZoomDown  2, 3</strong></td><td><strong><em>(reduce image no 2 and put the reduction in Gallery position 3)</em></strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Include  12, 3, 100, 1400</strong></td><td><strong><em>(include your logo (image no 12) in image 3, at position (100, 1400) )</em></strong></td>
</tr>
<td><strong>ToClipboard 3</strong></td><td><strong><em>(put final image no 3 in the system Clipboard)</em><strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>ExecTask WinWord.exe form3.dot</strong></td><td><strong><em>(run Word, execute macro form3.dot and retrieve the image in your form!)</em></strong></td>
</tr>

</table>
<p>
<strong>
<dl>
<dt><em>Want to automatically grab a slow scan image of 768x512, integrate 4 scans, and resize it to compensate for the tilt distortion?</em>
<dd>
</dl>
<p>
Create the following macro:-</br>
</strong>
<p>
<table cellpadding=14>
<tr>
<td><strong>GetSemSpeed t, v</strong></td><td><strong><em>(measure the SEM speed)</em></strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>GrabSlowScan 6, v, 5, 1, 4, 0</strong</td><td><strong><em>(grab image no 6 with some options)</strong</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Resize 6, 768, 600</strong></td><td><strong><em>(resize it as 768 x 600 to compensate for tilt distortion)</strong></em></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>
<dl>
<h3><dt><img src="../bullet.gif" align=top>2. Additional information</h3>
<p>
<dd>A number of buttons in the Orion software can be programmed to execute macro command files. With the INITBUTTON command you can define which .CMD file has to be linked with a button, and which icon has to be displayed in it. A macro command editor is included in the Orion software.
</dl>
</strong>
<p>
<p>
<center><strong><a href="#about">Return to about...</A></strong></center>
<p>
<p>


<a name="word1">
<strong>
<dl>
<dt><h3><img src="../bullet.gif" align=top>Macro commands and extensions for Word 6</h3>
<p>
<dd>Since a lot of SEM users are using Microsoft Word 6 for printing documents with included images, we can provide you with a number of macro commands specifically designed for manipulating images safely and integrate them in a Word document.
Although designing a macro file for Word can be quite simple, it can be really time consuming to design a really safe macro.
We can provide you with macros and technical assistance. 
<p>
The company to contact for developing macros for external applications is located in France:
I.C.I. sarl
tel (33) 84 58 02 43
fax (33) 84 54 03 98
</dl>
</strong>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<center><strong><a href="#about">Return to about...</A></strong></center>
<p>
<p>
<a name="word2">
<strong>
<dl>
<dt><h3><img src="../bullet.gif" align=top>Macro commands and extensions for Word 6 the Philips XL SEMs</h3>
<p>
<dd>We have more specific solutions for the Philips XL series. These SEMs can easily be upgraded with an Orion system, in order to get much more resolution in X, Y and gray levels.
Also very special macros have been designed, that process .TIF images generated by the XL microscope. The images data (accel. voltage, working distance, micron bar ...) are extracted and reproduced at the exact scale in the Word 6 document, making their use much easier.
</dl>
</strong>
<br>
<br>
<center>
