<HEAD>
<TITLE>MICSCAPE - BRUNEL MICROSCOPES ON-LINE CATALOGUE  </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<center>
<h3>BRUNEL MICROSCOPES LTD<BR>
On-line Catalogue of Microscopes and Accessories<BR><P>
Page 1</h3>
</center>
<hr>
<!-Page 1 image 1 TP Stereomicroscope->
<h3>TP STEREOMICROSCOPE - Price: 78.00 UK pounds</h3>
<img src="brun1i1.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=left>

This is a well constructed, full size professional standand 
stereomicroscope, available at a very economic price.The excellent 
quality x10 <b>widefield eyepieces</b> are fitted wth eyecups as standard. The 
interocular distance is adjustable between 51 -75mm to suit the 
individual, and one eyepiece can be focused independently 
The TP has a x2 fixed objective pair of excellent optical quality, 
giving the microscope an overall x20 magnification, which can be 
extended with additional eyepieces to give a <b>x20 - x40</b> potential range. 
The TP stereomicroscope has a rack and pinion fine focus system with a 
pillar coarse focus.The heavy base measures 160 x 115mm, and has a 
central translucent working table of 50mm diameter with two stage 
clips.This stereo is particularly recommended for its quality optical 
parts, versatility and most economic price, and is suitable for 
<b>photomicrography</b>. Accessories include additional eyepieces and case. 
<p>
<b>Accessories:-</b><br>
<p>

<pre>
     x15 eyepieces      - (BM938) - 22.00 Pounds/pair
     x20 eyepieces      - (BM931) - 24.00 Pounds/pair
     Wooden case        - (BM726) -  7.00 Pounds 
     Camera attachment  - (BM783) - 21.00 Pounds
     T2 ring            - (BM940) -  9.00 Pounds (please state camera make)
</pre>

<p>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!-Page 1 image 2 SX Dissection microscope->

<h3>BRUNEL SX DISSECTION MICROSCOPE - Price: 25.00 Pounds</h3>
<img src="brun1i2.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=right>
The Brunel SX is a purpose-built dissection microscope with a monocular
eyetube. Complete wth x10 and x20 eyepieces, the SX gives a choice of 
overall x10 or x20 magnification. The lens.system is supported by a 
multi-lever arm system, allowing it to be moved easily and smoothly to 
any position over the dissection area The microscope has a robust rack 
and pinion focus system and a glass plate dissection platform with 
detachable metal hand rests. A substantial mirror with fully rotating 
gimbal provides transmitted illumination if required. 
<P>
The quality and finish of this microscope is excellent, making it ideal 
for insect and small object dissection and manipulations.The microscope 
is complete wth a wooden carrying case with lock and key. The SX is 
also an economic monocular introduction to low-power microscopy. 
<p>
<br>
<br>
<center><h2>MAGNIFIERS</h2></center>
<img src="brun1i3.gif" alt="" hspace=12 align=left>

<b>We can provide a complete range of hand magnifiers:</b>
<br>
<pre>
(a) Flash Magnifier   (b) Hand magnifier 
(c) Double lens loupe (d) Watchmakers Eyeglass
(e) Large Loupe       (f) Small Loupe
(g) Folding Pocket    (h) Combination Loupe
</pre>
<p>
<br>
<br>

<pre>
(a) Flash Magnifier:   x5, 50mm lens with gauge. Steel chrome plated body.
                           Presentation box. Excellent quality- 10.00 pounds.

(b) Hand Magnifier:    x4, 2"x4" Rect. reader. Chrome plated brass frame
                           with black ebonite handle- 7.00 pounds.

(c) Double Lens Loupe: x15 Execellent quality. Finished in black with a
                           light transmitting skirt- 6.00 pounds.

(d) Watchmakers Glass: Superior quality finished in black, with 23.5mm diam.
                           lens. 1.5 inch (26D), 2.5 inch (16D) or 4 inch 
                           (10D) focus- 3.00 pounds.

(e) Large Loupe:       x10 21mm diam. lens system in a chrome plated brass
                           frame and housing. Double lens- 6.00 pounds.

(f) Small Loupe:       x10 15mm diam. lens system in a chrome plated zinc
                           frame- 3.00 pounds.

(g) Folding Pocket:    Folding triple lens system in black plastic frame and
                           housing. Very versatile unit- 4.00 pounds.

(h) Combination Loupe: x8  and x15 large combination double loupe. Housed in 
                           vinyl case and fully demountable for cleaning.
                           An excellent lens system- 12.00 pounds.
</pre>

