<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>MICSCAPE - BRUNEL MICROSCOPES ON-LINE CATALOGUE  </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<center>
<h3>BRUNEL MICROSCOPES LTD<BR>
On-line Catalogue of Microscopes and Accessories<BR><P>
Page 2</h3>
</center>
<hr>
<center>
<h3>MX SERIES STEREOMICROSCOPES <br>
Price Range: 85.00  to 190.00 UK pounds</h3>
<img src="brun2i1.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=left>
</center>
<h3>MX2 & MX3 Illustrated.</h3>
The MX series is a range of stereomicroscopes that combines durability with
value for money. Finished to a <b>high standard,</b> the MX series provides
an impressive range of specifications. The models are equipped with a choice of
incident or <b>incident/transmitted illumination.</b> For economy, the MXB and
MX-1 are also available <b>without</b> inbuilt lighting.
<p>
Each model is fitted with paired x10 widefield eyepieces and a choice of turret-mounted
or slide changer objectives. Accessories include additional eyepieces and objectives
which can provide a magnification range of <b>x10 to x120</b> for the slide changer models.

<p>
All binocular heads have dioptric adjustment and the interocular distance
can be varied to suit the individual. Eyecups and dustcover are provided 
as standard. Coarse focus is by pillar adjustment with a robust rack and 
pinion system providing fine movement. The MX series are particularly well
suited to photomicrography.
<p>

<h3>Model specifications:-</h3>
<dl>
<dt><b>MX - B </b>
<dd><b>Upright</b> binocular head with slide changer objectives. 
Substantial and stable base, complete with stage clips and removable dissection
plate. x2 objective pair in slide changer mount. x10 widefield eyepieces.
<p>
<dt><b>MX - 1 Price: 85.00 UK pounds</b>
<dd><b>Inclined</b> binocular head with the same base stand as
the MXB. x2 objective pair in slide changer mount. x10 widefield eyepieces
<p>
<dt><b>MX - 2 Price: 125.00 UK pounds</b>
<dd>Inclined binocular head with x2 slide changer objectives. x10 
widefield eyepieces. The base incorporates a 10-watt <b>illumination</b> system providing
incident illumination directed onto  the stage plate.
<p>
<dt><b>MX - 3 Price: 145.00 UK pounds</b>
<dd>Inclined stereohead as for the MX-2. In addtion, the MX-3
has a raised base, accommodating a second light source for <b>transmitted illumination</b>
to augment the <b>incident lighting.</b> A toggle switch is used to select the system
to be used. The MX-3 s a particularly versatile model, finished to a high standard
and represents excellent value combined with optical flexibility.
</dl>

<p>
<br>
<img src="brun2i2.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=right>
<b>MX series stereomicroscopes</b> are also available with turret-mounted twin objective 
pairs which may be either (xl/x3) or (x2/x4) giving models an inbuilt choice between
<b>x10/x30</b> or <b>x20/x40 magnification,</b> depending on model. The objective pairs of
the turret models ( 4T, 5T, 6T, 7T ) are fitted at the time of manufacture 
and cannot be replaced with the accessory objectives available for the
MX B, I, 2 and 3 models. However the accessory eyepieces fit all 
models and can be used to widen the  magnification range of the turret instruments.
<p>

<dl>
<dt><b>MX-4T Price: 170.00 UK pounds</b>
<dd>Inclined stereohead with x10 widefield eye pieces, inbuilt illumination, x1/x3 turret-mounted
objectives. Magnification x10 and x30.
<p>
<dt><b>MX-5T Price: 170.00 UK pounds</b>
<dd>As for the MX-4T, with x2/x4 objective options, giving a magnification of x20 and x40.
<p>
<dt><b>MX-6T Price: 190.00 UK pounds</b>
<dd>Optical specification as for the MX-4T but with inbuilt incident and transmitted lighting.
<p>
<dt><b>MX-7T Price: 190.00 UK pounds</b>
<dd>Optical specification as for the MX-5T, but with inbuilt incident and transmitted lighting.
</dl>
<p>
<h3>Accessories:-</h3>
<b>Objectives  (MXB, MX-1, 2, 3 only)</b>
<pre>
          x1 paired          (BM921) - 20.00 UK pounds
          x3 paired          (BM923) - 20.00 UK pounds
          x4 paired          (BM924) - 20.00 UK pounds
          x6 paired          (BM925) - 22.00 UK pounds
</pre>
<p>
<b>Eyepieces   (all models)</b>
<pre>
          x15 widefield (pair)             (BM926) - 35.00 UK pounds
          x20 widefield (pair)             (BM942) - 35.00 UK pounds
          Spare bulb                       (BM935) -  3.00 UK pounds
          Wooden case                      (BM932) -  8.00 UK pounds
          Photomicrography attachment      (BM939) - 21.00 UK pounds
          T2 ring (state camera make)      (BM940) -  9.00 UK pounds
          Dark Ground Attachment                   - 32.00 UK pounds
</pre>
<p>
<br>
<h1>GEMSCOPES</h1>
<img src="brun2i3.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=right>

The MX models that have inbuilt transmitted illumination (MX-3, 6T, 7T),
can be converted either at the time of purchase or via the accessories
option to specialist <b>gem stereomicroscopes</b> with a <b>darkfield</b> attachment
plate fitted in place of the large dissection plate. A gemclamp may also
be fitted in place of one of the base spring clips.
<p>
In addition a simple <b>polariser/analyser</b> set can be attached to the support
column of any of the range, however this is much more effective for those
models with transmitted illumination.
<p>


Further accessories include a <b>drawing attachment</b> and x10 widefield
<b>micrometer eyepiece</b> to be used in conjunction with a stage micrometer.
<p>

<pre>
     Dark field attachment             (BM310) 
     x10 eyepiece with micrometer      (BM311)  
     Stage micrometer                  (BM312)  
     Drawing attachment - prism type   (BM313)  
     Drawing attachment - mirror type  (BM314) 
</pre>
<p>
The MX stereomicroscopes represents an excellent value for money series of 
instruments and are highly recommended for all applications
<p>
<br>
