<h4><i>The Wedmore SP series Microscopes are now available with a four position turret as 
an optional extra. Ideal for those proposing to use a wide magnification range. Should you
require a four position turret, mark your order clearly and 5.00 UK Pounds surcharge to the
cost of all Wedmore models.</i></h4>
<p>

<h3>Drawing Attachment (BML003) Price: 19.00 UK Pounds</h3>

<IMG SRC="brun3i3.gif" alt="" align=right hspace=12>
The traditional camera lucida, or drawing attachment, is an accessory rarely
available, and yet is of great value to those who prefer a drawing record 
system to photography. Two units are available using either a prism system
which allows the observer to see both an image of the specimen superimposed
on to paper at the base of the microscope and , at the same time, a pen or
pencil or alternatively a mirror reflection system. With either system the
subject matter can simply be traced. Adaptors are available to convert
either type for stereomicroscopes. Both units will fit directly on to the
eyetubes of all compound microscopes listed in our current catalogue as
well as most others. In general terms the prism type is best suited to
mirror illumination microscopes and the mirror system is more effective
with microscopes that have in built illumination.

<p>
<br>
<h3>WEDMORE  SX  ADVANCED  MICROSCOPE <br>
Price: 195.00 UK Pounds</h3>
<IMG SRC="brun3i2.gif" alt="" align=Left hspace=12>


The SX301 is a high build quality microscope ideal for advanced school
and university course work, as well as for the discerning enthusiast.
The instrument is based on an enlarged and improved SP stand, with a finish
and attention to detail unequalled in a microscope of this price range.
<p>
The microscope has a <b>quadruple</b> objective turret, and is complete with x5,
x10, x45 and x100 (oil immersion) achromatic objectives giving an excellent
optical performance. The x6, x10 and x15 eyepieces provide a <b>magnification
range from x30 - x1500.</b> Particularly impressive is the large <b>integral
mechanical stage</b> with low position drop down coaxial controls, permitting
a combination of controlled movements. The stage is complete with double 
vernier scales which allows exact repositioning of slide subjects for
further study. The instrument has a separate coarse and fine focus
adjustment, with the latter being graduated for depth measurement.
<p>
The substage <b>condenser</b> has a separate rack and pinion focus control and is
complete with <b>iris diaphragm and filter carrier.</b> Illumination is by a
plano/concave mirror system or alternatively by a 240v detachable <b>lamp</b> unit
which fits in place of the mirror.
<p>
The SX301 is finished in grey enamel to
a high standard and is complete with wooden carrying case. The unit weighs
approximately 4 kilograms with a maximum height of 340mm.
<p>
