<center>
<h3>WESTBURY SP30 & SP40 SERIES MICROSCOPES<br>
Price Range: 104.00  to 305.00 UK pounds</h3>
<img src="brun4i1.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=RIGHT>
</center>

<!-Page 9 ->

The <B>SP30</B> high powered microscope is a robust, well designed instrument 
finished to an excellent standard. The impressive specifications of this
range are considered ideal for the advanced student or enthusiast.The eye
tube units (both <B><I>monocular</I></B> and <B><I>binocular</I></B>) are inclined and fully rotatable
through 360 degrees with high performance x10 eyepieces. The rack and pini
on coarse focus mechanism provides 50mm of vertical movement, and the fine
focus mechanism has a notably smooth action with a range of 2mm. The large
square stage can be fitted with either a <B>mechanical specimen driver</B> with 
double vernier scales or slide clips depending on the model.
<P>
Irrespective of model type all microscopes are equipped with a full 
substage which includes an <B>Abbe condenser</B> with independent focus control 
(NA 1.25) and iris diaphragm. Specimen slides may be protected by a <B>focus 
stop</B> mechanism which may be adjusted to prevent over focus and damage to 
the high power objectives.

<!-Page 9 Image 1 Westbury  SP30 ->

The four position objective turret can be equipped with a choice from 
<B>x4, x10, x40, x63 or x100 (oil) objectives</B>, that are parfocal and of
excellent quality, with rubber syling inserts.

The models with inbuilt illumination have a 15 watt system controlled by 
an on/off switch, and have a <B>field focusing lens</B>, which can be easily
removed for bulb replacement. The large heavy base gives the Westbury
SP30 particular stability for a microscope of this class, and the mirror 
illumination models can be upgraded to inbuilt illumination at a later 
date after purchase if required.

This is a particularly well designed series of microscopes with a wide
range of accessories which includes a <B>BINOCULAR</B> head rarely available 
for microscopes of this budget price.
<P>

