<center>
<h2>BRUNEL SP-10 ADVANCED MICROSCOPE<br>
Price Range: 420.00  to 600.00 UK pounds</h2>
<img src="brun5i1.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=RIGHT>
</center>
<h3>BRUNEL SP-10 ADVANCED MICROSCOPE</h3>
<p>
<b>The Brunel SP-10 is an advanced research standard microscope with an 
excellent finish and impressive optical performance. This range is avaliable
exclusively from Brunel Microscopes and is recommended as a quality 
microscope in either monocular, binocular or trinocular form.
</b>
<p>
The SP-10 has a four position objective turret with a precise internal index
ng mechanism. The DIN standard objectives are parfocal achromats with a 
rubber insert styling grip, and are matched with extremely widefield x10 
compensating eyepieces. The microscope heads are rotatable through 360 
degrees and have full eyetube dioptric adjustment. The trinocular head 
allows full light to the binocular element, or an 80/20 to the trinocular 
tube.
<p>
<pre>
           Achromatic Objectives      Numerical Aperature
           ---------------------      -------------------
           x4                            N.A.  0.10
           x10                           N.A.  0.25
           x40                           N.A.  0.65
           x100                          N.A.  1.25

</pre>

<!- Page 15 Image 1 Brunel SP-10 Binocular->

The large mechanical stage measures 160mm x 150mm and has  well positioned 
drop down coaxial controls with a double vernier. The substage condenser
(N.A. 1.25) has a full rack and pinion control mechanism and is equipped 
with an iris diaphragm and 32mm filter carrier.
<p>

<img src="brun5i2.gif" alt="" hspace=12 vspace=6 align=left>

The SP-10 has been elegantly
designed and is finished in grey enamel, and has a build quality equal to in
struments of far greater cost that are considered the optical market leaders.
The microscope has low position coaxial coarse and fine focus controls, with
an adjustable <b>tension control</b> and <b>auto focus.</b> In addition the SP-10 has a 
fully adjustable focus stop to protect the high power objectives. 
<p>
The integrated solid state electronics controls a 6volt 20 watt tungsten 
<b>halogen</b> light source via an integral fuse, on/off switch, rheostat 
brightness control and indicator warning light. The bulb may be accessed 
via a simple trap door mechanism in the base of the instrument. The full 
field illumination is generated by a multiple element field lens.
<p>
The SP-10 can also be supplied with <b>planchromatic</b> objectives, <b>photomicrography</b>
and CCTV equipment. The range of accessories is extensive and includes <b>phase
contrast</b> objectives with matching condenser rings that are available for 
each magnification. This allows the selection of specific objectives without
the cost of a full phase contrast set for all the magnification range. 
Simple polarisation accessories can also be fitted.
<p>
<br>
<center><h3>Accessories for SP10 Microscopes</h3></center>
<p>
The SP10 series has a wide range of accessories which allow the microscopes
to be used for many applications, and facilitates 'tailoring' of the instrument
to individual specifications and use. <B>Prices for the following accessories
are available <a href="mailto:"101353.3301@compuserve.com">on request.</A></b>
<p>
<pre>
	Photomicrography attachment	(SP100)
