<A name="about">
<p>
<B>ABOUT MOLCOL SOFTWARE</B><BR>
Molcol Software (that's me) are the pioneers of Microscopy Software for general and educational use. Our Version 3.0
of Microscope for the PC is already in use at schools in different countries and by the general public at home. This 
'First in the world' virtual microscope package enables all people to enjoy the incredible world of the very small 
without any additional hardware except a standard PC. Four years in the making, it brings a major tool to the world's
educationalists, it's people, and existing Microscopists.
<p>
The project is run as a commercial venture only because such protocols are needed under the UK taxation system. All 
profits received by me trading as Molcol Software is used to further the promotion of Microscopy, Biology, and 
their importance and enjoyment to more people in the world. It is a personal endeavour driven by love and respect
for the study of life. Most of the funds received are now used to support this web site in the UK.
<P>
<center><a href="#top">Top of Page</A></center>
<P>
<B>TRY MICROSCOPE for the PC NOW</B><BR>
A shareware version of Microscope for the PC has been made available to show all features of the Registered version. You 
can download the software to your PC from this page. Several electronic slidesets have been converted to shareware use and
can also be downloaded to show the scope and range of material available. If you would like to know more about this amazing
new tool then <A HREF="mailto:mol@molcol.demon.co.uk"> why not drop me a note.</A>
The software will work in DOS, Windows 3.x, and Windows 95.
<P>
