<A NAME="VER3 DOWNLOAD">
<BR>
<H3>Microscope for the PC Ver. 3.0 Shareware (Download Guide)</H3>
This is a large comprehensive package which emulates using a microscope on your PC.
The software <B>will work on any IBM compatible PC</B> in DOS, Windows 3.1, and Windows 95.
You will be able to see 'still' slidesets and video images, magnify up to 1000x in 
real resolution, move around images, re-focus them, control time-lapse sequences,
and much much more. <strong> Both parts 1 and 2 must be downloaded </strong>. The zipped files
are very large, so give yourself plenty of time to download them. After both files 
have been down-loaded to the same directory, you must use PKUNZIP to extract the 
software from the compressed files. Use Notepad or any other WINDOWS or DOS text editor to view 
the 'read.me' files once the software has been 'unzipped' onto your hard-drive. 

<P>
<center><a href="#top">Top of Page</A></center>
<p>

<A NAME="SETS DOWNLOAD">
<H3>EXTRA SLIDESETS</H3>
Once you've downloaded Microscope for the PC and recovered from the stunning discovery
that you can go 'scoping' from your armchair, you might be hungry to see more slidesets.
Well now you can from these pages. If you just want to download one of them, try the last one
in the list provided. This is the most recent. When the file is safely on your disk, unzip it and 
PLEASE read the read.me file to understand how to install the slideset for use with Microscope
for the PC.<BR>
<p>
<BR>

<P>
<center><a href="#top">Top of Page</A></center>
<p>

<A NAME="DEMO DOWNLOAD">
<H3>DEMO ONLY Microscope for the PC - quick download</H3>
Downloading the large files for Microscope for the PC Part1 and Part2 is a lengthy process. You may feel it might not be worth 
while. Just to convince you that the time is well spent, you can download a DEMO only version which will transfer to your PC
much faster. Once you have unzipped the file and had a 'taste' of 'Scoping' on your PC, you'll soon be back for the real thing.
<p>
<BR>

<P>
<center><a href="#top">Top of Page</A></center>
<p>

<A NAME="WALL DOWNLOAD">
<H3>Microscope for the PC - WALLPAPERS</H3>
Two packs of stunning Microscopy images ready to use as
Windows Wallpapers can be downloaded now. If you love Microscopy, you're 
going to love these images!
<p>
<BR>

<P>
<center><a href="#top">Top of Page</A></center>
<p>

<A NAME="FREE DOWNLOAD">
<H3>Royalty-Free Microscopy pictures from Molcol Software</H3>
Just yours for the asking: a set of free images straight down to your PC
now. A gift from Molcol Software to encourage greater interest in Microscopy
and Biology. You will need to use an image viewer to see these once they are unzipped.
<br>
<P>
<center><a href="#top">Top of Page</A></center>
<p>

<BR>
<A NAME="SEM DOWNLOAD">
<H3>SEM IMAGES</H3>
Microscopix Photo-Library in the UK specialise in providing images of microscopic subjects for publishers, advertisers, and educationalists.
Their use of a Scanning Electron Microscope (SEM) enables incredible detailed images to be produced. Now you can
see them yourself. Microscopix has made a set of SEM images available for shareware use on your own PC. You can download this
set so that the unzipped images will be in your chosen format.<BR>

<P>
<center><a href="#top">Top of Page</A></center>
<p>

<A NAME="other">
<H3>GAMES</H3>
