<center><img src="hairs1s.jpg" width=320 height=272 border=1></center>
<br clear>
<FONT COLOR="0000FF" SIZE=6>

<br>
This is a low power shot of hairs found on a N.Zealand Daisy Bush, <em>Olearia haastii</em>. It is seen here
in polarized light. I scrapped the surface of a leaf and deposited the 'scrappings'
into a dollop of Fructose Solution. Pretty neat, huh?
<br>
<center><img src="hairs2s.jpg" width=284 height=267 border=1></center>
<br clear>
Here's another shot of it taken at a higher power! You can make slides like this easily...
trust me, cos I am a rank amateur and I found it easier than working my video recorder.
