<HEAD>
<TITLE>www.microscopy-uk.org.uk - Micscape : Amateur mag. on paper</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<a name="top">
<BODY background="peop.gif" TEXT="#000066" VLINK="#7F3F7F" LINK="#CF3FCF">


<center><h1>The UK Amateurs launch non-profit magazine!</h1></center>
<p>
<center><img src="magcov.jpg" width=236 height=329></center>
<br clear>
<strong>
<h3>Amateurs launch paper magazine</h3>
<em>Well, if we don't blow our own trumpets - who else will?</em>
<p>
We got so frustrated about the fact that many of the thousands of amateur
microscopists in the UK are not on the web, we decided to find a way for 
them to share in the excitement. We put the best bits of Micscape (our 
electronic mag.) together and printed out 84 pages complete with a colour 
cover and offered it out to the amateurs here at cost price. Okay, we admit
the quality is fairly basic with each copy consisting of a photocopy of the 
master copy, although every one has its own freshly printed colour printed 
cover.
<p>
We asked for 3.00 UK pounds per copy and run out of the first print right 
away. The amount of work involved was considerable and we actually lose a bit
of money on every issue posted out due to high costs of photocopying and
postage, but at least now some of the amateurs here get to share the 
amateur microscopy WEB experience. 
<p>
You never know but if we could get enough interest from around the world
maybe, just maybe, we could get something similar more widely circulated 
to all those people not on the web?!
<p>
The magazine is produced twice a year for the time being but don't worry 
that you won't probaly ever see an issue: <em>you have the real thing here
on the web</em>. Why not take a look at this month's issue of <a href="../mag/indexmag.html">Micscape 
Magazine</A>
