<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>www.microscopy-uk.org.uk - Feedback and site stats</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<a name="top">
<BODY background="peop.gif" TEXT="#000066" VLINK="#7F3F7F" LINK="#CF3FCF">
<center><img src="feedback.gif" width=419 height=142></center>
<br clear>

<center><h1>Feedback and Stats at Microscopy UK</h1></center>
<p>
<strong>
In a world driven by the pressure of modern commercialism, it is difficult to envisage 
any area where people motivated by nothing more than curiosity and intrigue 
for living things can have a say in what is important in their lives. Microscopy, by its
very name alone, seems to promote imagery of a pursuit fit only for the ardent 
study into searching out secrets for commercial exploitation, yet nothing could be further
from the truth. Microscopy is one of the few <em>true</em> interests that anyone 
can become involved with and enjoy for its own sake.
<p>
Here at Microscopy UK we are endeavouring not only to keep this interest alive in 
a modern environment - we are succeeding in bringing the subject out of a dusty Victorian 
cupboard and repositioning it as the lively subject it actually is. 
<p>
<em>And every reader and visitor is helping us to do it. Well done!</em>
<p>
This page enables you to get a tiny feel of the interaction going on between 
all of amateurs as well as the professionals who still remember their initial passion  - and through it -
are prepared to become involved!
<p>
All are welcome! All information exchanges are in the spirit of sharing...
<p>

<center>
<h3>
<a href="#who">Who's visiting Microscopy UK</A><br>
<a href="#share">'Sharemail' of the moment</A><br>

<a href="paper1.html">New <em>Profitless</em> paper magazine launched</A><br>
<a href="../project/jointven.html">Worldwide Amateur Project 1</A><br>
