 available from these pages. Movie files are stored on Micscapeas compressed (self-extracting) executable files - that is: you need to <b>Run</b> them first after downloadingthem to extract the real movie file or files.<p>The Movie Player expects a movie file to be a <b>M{number}.QPL</b> file. All movie filenames start with the letter 'M' and havea suffix of '.QPL'. The rest of the filename consists of a sequence of numbers. The filename must not be altered in any way!! An example of an extracted movie filename is: M1295513.QPL<br><br><center><h4><em><a href="#about">Sub-Index</A> / <a href="#movietop"> Button Selector</A></em></h4></center><br><br> <a name="player"><p><H3>The Movie Player</H3>Micscape Movies can only be played back by using Micscape's special movie player software. This is <b>very special software</b> because it allows you to see real-time animation on a wide range of hardware and software platforms. We could make it into a 'helper' application for Netscape but it seems quicker and cheaper for you to simply bring movies down to your PC and run them off-line. If you think a helper application would be better then <a href="mailto:mol@molcol.demon.co.uk">drop us a line.</A><br><br><center><h4><em><a href="#about">Sub-Index</A> / <a href="#movietop"> Button Selector</A></em></h4></center><br><br> <a name="compat"><p><h3>Compatibility</h3>The player will run micscape movies on all of these: <i>286, 386, 486, &  Pentium Processors; on any speed processor <b>even SX16's</b>, any VGA card - as long as it is a colour VGA - from VGA to SVGA; it will work under most forms of DOS from MSDOS 3.1 to 7.0, Norton DOS, PCDOS, etc.</I> It will also run underWindows from 3.0 to Win95 in a DOS session. You don't need any other software like mpeg players, special drivers,nor do you need a mouse, soundblaster card, or a fast access hard disk. The Micscape Movie Player was designed by Molcol Software to show the incredible life-forms and the savage beauty of our Microscopic world. The softwarehas been created to be as hardware and software independent as possible, except for the limitation that it can onlybe used on IBM compatible PCs <em> or possibly MAC computers</em> (see below).<H3>MAC computers</h3>The Movie Player has been reported to work fine on a MAC computer using Soft 'Windows', although we (the amateurs) havenot tested it ourselves!<br><br><center><h4><em><a href="#about">Sub-Index</A> / <a href="#movietop"> Button Selector</A></em></h4></center><br><br> <p><a name="free"><h3>Conditions of use</h3>And the good news is: <b>you can use it for as long as you like without paying for it!</b>
The Micscape Movie Player, and the movies it is designed to work with, are SHAREWARE but with a vital difference. You can use it for as long as you want to <i>payment-free</i> simply by emailing us and registering your payment-free use.Simply <b><A HREF="mailto:mol@molcol.demon.co.uk">contact us</A></b> stating your real name and address, your e-mail address, and a one-liner saying "I'm registering for payment-free use". <br><br>
