<TITLE>Microscopy UK / MICSCAPE - 3D Stereo Microscopy : Sheep Tick</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#000000" text="#00ff00">

<a name="top">

<P>
<center><h1>3D Sheep Tick</h1></center>
<center><em>Wait for image to load... it's worth it!</em></center>
<br>

<center><IMG SRC="3dtick.jpg" width=315 height=238></center>
<p>
<h4>
The next time you put on your wellies and creep out in the middle of the 
night to keep a lonely sheep company, you mind like to consider the sort 
of company some sheep keep... like this female <em>Ixodes ricinus</em>,
a common ectoparasitic tick of sheep and deer (the long word indicates the parasite 
lives externally on the sheep). This parasite is a vector of Lyme disease although
this is not a common problem in this country (the UK).
<p>
This incredible 3D SEM image was captured by Andrew Syred on our our small 
crew of enthusiasts here. 

</h4>
