<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Microscopy UK / MICSCAPE - 3D Stereo Microscopy : Biology</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#000000" text="#00ff00">

<a name="top">

<P>
<center><h1>3D Mammalian Ovary</h1></center>
<p>

<center><IMG SRC="3dovary1.jpg"></center>
<h4>
This is a section through part of a mammalian ovary. The tiny rows
of cells are <em>primary follicles.</em> Some of these will ultimately
mature to form <strong>Graafian follicles</strong>.
<p>
The image was created by 'sampling' the source slide into a computer
from an optical microscope by using a camcorder. An image was 'taken', and
then the glass specimen slide was moved left before a second image
was shot. Boths images were then used with <A href="3dads.html#dv">Double Vision</A> software to form the 3D representation
you see here.
<p>
The depth of the specimen is very shallow so the 3D effect is slight.
<p>
</h4>
<H3>
<center>
<A HREF="3dfront.html#select">3D Image Selector</A>
