<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Microscopy UK / MICSCAPE - 3D Stereo Microscopy : Ant Head</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#000000" text="#00ff00">

<a name="top">

<P>
<center><h1>Hologram of Ant Head</h1></center>
<p>

<center><IMG SRC="3dant1.jpg"></center>
<p>
<h4>
Lean back away from your monitor and stare at the Ant head. You will 
need your red/blue glasses on. Give yourself around 20 seconds or so
and you should start to see the ant's head projected in front on the 
surface of the screen. It's slightly blurred and this defect
will probably create a slight strain on your eyes if you look  
for too long, but stay with it to get the effect!
<P>
<strong>For best effect:-</strong><br>
Look at the ant's jaws for a bit then
switch your gaze to the upper left antenna, and then to
the <em>Micscape</em> legend. Spend a few seconds on each and repeat 
the sequence, progressively staring longer at the antenna, and the ant's jaws.
Finally hold your gaze on the ant jaws and the front of the head!
<p>
This image was created from a single frame of a video film. It was
'sampled' into a PC and converted into a hologram using <A href="3dads.html#dv">Double Vision</A> software.
</h4>
